43class methods
44-------------
45
46It has some similarity to the byref() construct compared to pointer()

48 - construct an instance from a given memory block (sharing this memory block)
49
50from_param(obj)
51 - typecheck and convert a Python object into a C function call parameter
52 The result may be an instance of the type, or an integer or tuple
53 (typecode, value[, obj])
54
55instance methods/properties
56---------------------------
57
58_as_parameter_
59 - convert self into a C function call parameter
60 This is either an integer, or a 3-tuple (typecode, value, obj)

62functions
63---------

75pointer(cdata)
76
77POINTER(ctype)
78
79bytes(cdata)
80 - return the buffer contents as a sequence of bytes (which is currently a string)

133typedef struct {
134 PyObject_HEAD
135 PyObject *key;
136 PyObject *dict;
137} DictRemoverObject;
138
139static void
140_DictRemover_dealloc(PyObject *myself)
141{
142 DictRemoverObject *self = (DictRemoverObject *)myself;
143 Py_XDECREF(self->key);
144 Py_XDECREF(self->dict);
145 Py_TYPE(self)->tp_free(myself);
146}
147
148static PyObject *
149_DictRemover_call(PyObject *myself, PyObject *args, PyObject *kw)
150{
151 DictRemoverObject *self = (DictRemoverObject *)myself;
152 if (self->key && self->dict) {
153 if (-1 == PyDict_DelItem(self->dict, self->key))
154 /* XXX Error context */
155 PyErr_WriteUnraisable(Py_None);
156 Py_CLEAR(self->key);
157 Py_CLEAR(self->dict);
158 }
159 Py_RETURN_NONE;
160}

205int
206PyDict_SetItemProxy(PyObject *dict, PyObject *key, PyObject *item)
207{
208 PyObject *obj;
209 DictRemoverObject *remover;
210 PyObject *proxy;
211 int result;
212
213 obj = _PyObject_CallNoArg((PyObject *)&DictRemover_Type);
214 if (obj == NULL)
215 return -1;
216
217 remover = (DictRemoverObject *)obj;
218 assert(remover->key == NULL);
219 assert(remover->dict == NULL);
220 Py_INCREF(key);
221 remover->key = key;
222 Py_INCREF(dict);
223 remover->dict = dict;
224
225 proxy = PyWeakref_NewProxy(item, obj);
226 Py_DECREF(obj);
227 if (proxy == NULL)
228 return -1;
229
230 result = PyDict_SetItem(dict, key, proxy);
231 Py_DECREF(proxy);
232 return result;
233}
234
235PyObject *
236PyDict_GetItemProxy(PyObject *dict, PyObject *key)
237{
238 PyObject *result;
239 PyObject *item = PyDict_GetItem(dict, key);
240
241 if (item == NULL)
242 return NULL;
243 if (!PyWeakref_CheckProxy(item))
244 return item;
245 result = PyWeakref_GET_OBJECT(item);
246 if (result == Py_None)
247 return NULL;
248 return result;
249}

253/*
254 Allocate a memory block for a pep3118 format string, filled with
255 a suitable PEP 3118 type code corresponding to the given ctypes
256 type. Returns NULL on failure, with the error indicator set.
257
258 This produces type codes in the standard size mode (cf. struct module),
259 since the endianness may need to be swapped to a non-native one
260 later on.
261 */
262static char *
263_ctypes_alloc_format_string_for_type(char code, int big_endian)
264{
265 char *result;
266 char pep_code = '\0';
267
268 switch (code) {
269#if SIZEOF_INT == 2
270 case 'i': pep_code = 'h'; break;
271 case 'I': pep_code = 'H'; break;
272#elif SIZEOF_INT == 4
273 case 'i': pep_code = 'i'; break;
274 case 'I': pep_code = 'I'; break;
275#elif SIZEOF_INT == 8
276 case 'i': pep_code = 'q'; break;
277 case 'I': pep_code = 'Q'; break;
278#else
279# error SIZEOF_INT has an unexpected value
280#endif /* SIZEOF_INT */
281#if SIZEOF_LONG == 4
282 case 'l': pep_code = 'l'; break;
283 case 'L': pep_code = 'L'; break;
284#elif SIZEOF_LONG == 8
285 case 'l': pep_code = 'q'; break;
286 case 'L': pep_code = 'Q'; break;
287#else
288# error SIZEOF_LONG has an unexpected value
289#endif /* SIZEOF_LONG */
290#if SIZEOF__BOOL == 1
291 case '?': pep_code = '?'; break;
292#elif SIZEOF__BOOL == 2
293 case '?': pep_code = 'H'; break;
294#elif SIZEOF__BOOL == 4
295 case '?': pep_code = 'L'; break;
296#elif SIZEOF__BOOL == 8
297 case '?': pep_code = 'Q'; break;
298#else
299# error SIZEOF__BOOL has an unexpected value
300#endif /* SIZEOF__BOOL */
301 default:
302 /* The standard-size code is the same as the ctypes one */
303 pep_code = code;
304 break;
305 }
306
307 result = PyMem_Malloc(3);
308 if (result == NULL)
309 return NULL;
310
311 result[0] = big_endian ? '>' : '<';
312 result[1] = pep_code;
313 result[2] = '\0';
314 return result;
315}

317/*
318 Allocate a memory block for a pep3118 format string, copy prefix (if
319 non-null) and suffix into it. Returns NULL on failure, with the error
320 indicator set. If called with a suffix of NULL the error indicator must
321 already be set.
322 */
323char *
324_ctypes_alloc_format_string(const char *prefix, const char *suffix)
325{
326 size_t len;
327 char *result;
328
329 if (suffix == NULL) {
330 assert(PyErr_Occurred());
331 return NULL;
332 }
333 len = strlen(suffix);
334 if (prefix)
335 len += strlen(prefix);
336 result = PyMem_Malloc(len + 1);
337 if (result == NULL) {
338 PyErr_NoMemory();
339 return NULL;
340 }
341 if (prefix)
342 strcpy(result, prefix);
343 else
344 result[0] = '\0';
345 strcat(result, suffix);
346 return result;
347}
348
349/*
350 Allocate a memory block for a pep3118 format string, adding
351 the given prefix (if non-null), an additional shape prefix, and a suffix.
352 Returns NULL on failure, with the error indicator set. If called with
353 a suffix of NULL the error indicator must already be set.
354 */
355char *
356_ctypes_alloc_format_string_with_shape(int ndim, const Py_ssize_t *shape,
357 const char *prefix, const char *suffix)
358{
359 char *new_prefix;
360 char *result;
361 char buf[32];
362 Py_ssize_t prefix_len;
363 int k;
364
365 prefix_len = 32 * ndim + 3;
366 if (prefix)
367 prefix_len += strlen(prefix);
368 new_prefix = PyMem_Malloc(prefix_len);
369 if (new_prefix == NULL)
370 return NULL;
371 new_prefix[0] = '\0';
372 if (prefix)
373 strcpy(new_prefix, prefix);
374 if (ndim > 0) {
375 /* Add the prefix "(shape[0],shape[1],...,shape[ndim-1])" */
376 strcat(new_prefix, "(");
377 for (k = 0; k < ndim; ++k) {
378 if (k < ndim-1) {
379 sprintf(buf, "%"PY_FORMAT_SIZE_T"d,", shape[k]);
380 } else {
381 sprintf(buf, "%"PY_FORMAT_SIZE_T"d)", shape[k]);
382 }
383 strcat(new_prefix, buf);
384 }
385 }
386 result = _ctypes_alloc_format_string(new_prefix, suffix);
387 PyMem_Free(new_prefix);
388 return result;
389}

391/*
392 PyCStructType_Type - a meta type/class. Creating a new class using this one as
393 __metaclass__ will call the constructor StructUnionType_new. It replaces the
394 tp_dict member with a new instance of StgDict, and initializes the C
395 accessible fields somehow.
396*/
397
398static PyCArgObject *
399StructUnionType_paramfunc(CDataObject *self)
400{
401 PyCArgObject *parg;
402 StgDictObject *stgdict;
403
404 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
405 if (parg == NULL)
406 return NULL;
407
408 parg->tag = 'V';
409 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
410 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for structure/union instances */
411 parg->pffi_type = &stgdict->ffi_type_pointer;
412 /* For structure parameters (by value), parg->value doesn't contain the structure
413 data itself, instead parg->value.p *points* to the structure's data
414 See also _ctypes.c, function _call_function_pointer().
415 */
416 parg->value.p = self->b_ptr;
417 parg->size = self->b_size;
418 Py_INCREF(self);
419 parg->obj = (PyObject *)self;
420 return parg;
421}
422
423static PyObject *
424StructUnionType_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds, int isStruct)
425{
426 PyTypeObject *result;
427 PyObject *fields;
428 StgDictObject *dict;
429
430 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
431 since we are a metatype!) */
432 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, args, kwds);
433 if (!result)
434 return NULL;
435
436 /* keep this for bw compatibility */
437 if (PyDict_GetItemString(result->tp_dict, "_abstract_"))
438 return (PyObject *)result;
439
440 dict = (StgDictObject *)_PyObject_CallNoArg((PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type);
441 if (!dict) {
442 Py_DECREF(result);
443 return NULL;
444 }
445 /* replace the class dict by our updated stgdict, which holds info
446 about storage requirements of the instances */
447 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)dict, result->tp_dict)) {
448 Py_DECREF(result);
449 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)dict);
450 return NULL;
451 }
452 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)dict);
453 dict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string(NULL, "B");
454 if (dict->format == NULL) {
455 Py_DECREF(result);
456 return NULL;
457 }
458
459 dict->paramfunc = StructUnionType_paramfunc;
460
461 fields = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)dict, "_fields_");
462 if (!fields) {
463 StgDictObject *basedict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)result->tp_base);
464
465 if (basedict == NULL)
466 return (PyObject *)result;
467 /* copy base dict */
468 if (-1 == PyCStgDict_clone(dict, basedict)) {
469 Py_DECREF(result);
470 return NULL;
471 }
472 dict->flags &= ~DICTFLAG_FINAL; /* clear the 'final' flag in the subclass dict */
473 basedict->flags |= DICTFLAG_FINAL; /* set the 'final' flag in the baseclass dict */
474 return (PyObject *)result;
475 }
476
477 if (-1 == PyObject_SetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "_fields_", fields)) {
478 Py_DECREF(result);
479 return NULL;
480 }
481 return (PyObject *)result;
482}

500CDataType_from_address(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
501{

503 if (!PyLong_Check(value)) {
504 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,

514static const char from_buffer_doc[] =
515"C.from_buffer(object, offset=0) -> C instance\ncreate a C instance from a writeable buffer";
516
517static int
518KeepRef(CDataObject *target, Py_ssize_t index, PyObject *keep);
519
520static PyObject *
521CDataType_from_buffer(PyObject *type, PyObject *args)
522{
523 PyObject *obj;
524 PyObject *mv;
525 PyObject *result;
526 Py_buffer *buffer;
527 Py_ssize_t offset = 0;
528
529 StgDictObject *dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
530 if (!dict) {
531 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "abstract class");
532 return NULL;
533 }
534
535 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O|n:from_buffer", &obj, &offset))
536 return NULL;
537
538 mv = PyMemoryView_FromObject(obj);
539 if (mv == NULL)
540 return NULL;
541
542 buffer = PyMemoryView_GET_BUFFER(mv);
543
544 if (buffer->readonly) {
545 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
546 "underlying buffer is not writable");
547 Py_DECREF(mv);
548 return NULL;
549 }
550
551 if (!PyBuffer_IsContiguous(buffer, 'C')) {
552 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
553 "underlying buffer is not C contiguous");
554 Py_DECREF(mv);
555 return NULL;
556 }
557
558 if (offset < 0) {
559 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
560 "offset cannot be negative");
561 Py_DECREF(mv);
562 return NULL;
563 }
564
565 if (dict->size > buffer->len - offset) {
566 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
567 "Buffer size too small "
568 "(%zd instead of at least %zd bytes)",
569 buffer->len, dict->size + offset);
570 Py_DECREF(mv);
571 return NULL;
572 }
573
574 result = PyCData_AtAddress(type, (char *)buffer->buf + offset);
575 if (result == NULL) {
576 Py_DECREF(mv);
577 return NULL;
578 }
579
580 if (-1 == KeepRef((CDataObject *)result, -1, mv)) {
581 Py_DECREF(result);
582 return NULL;
583 }
584
585 return result;
586}

588static const char from_buffer_copy_doc[] =
589"C.from_buffer_copy(object, offset=0) -> C instance\ncreate a C instance from a readable buffer";
590
591static PyObject *
592GenericPyCData_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds);
593
594static PyObject *
595CDataType_from_buffer_copy(PyObject *type, PyObject *args)
596{
597 Py_buffer buffer;
598 Py_ssize_t offset = 0;
599 PyObject *result;
600 StgDictObject *dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
601 if (!dict) {
602 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "abstract class");
603 return NULL;
604 }
605
606 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "y*|n:from_buffer_copy", &buffer, &offset))
607 return NULL;
608
609 if (offset < 0) {
610 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
611 "offset cannot be negative");
612 PyBuffer_Release(&buffer);
613 return NULL;
614 }
615
616 if (dict->size > buffer.len - offset) {
617 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
618 "Buffer size too small (%zd instead of at least %zd bytes)",
619 buffer.len, dict->size + offset);
620 PyBuffer_Release(&buffer);
621 return NULL;
622 }
623
624 result = GenericPyCData_new((PyTypeObject *)type, NULL, NULL);
625 if (result != NULL) {
626 memcpy(((CDataObject *)result)->b_ptr,
627 (char *)buffer.buf + offset, dict->size);
628 }
629 PyBuffer_Release(&buffer);
630 return result;
631}

633static const char in_dll_doc[] =
634"C.in_dll(dll, name) -> C instance\naccess a C instance in a dll";
635
636static PyObject *
637CDataType_in_dll(PyObject *type, PyObject *args)
638{
639 PyObject *dll;
640 char *name;
641 PyObject *obj;
642 void *handle;
643 void *address;
644
645 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "Os:in_dll", &dll, &name))
646 return NULL;
647
648 obj = PyObject_GetAttrString(dll, "_handle");
649 if (!obj)
650 return NULL;
651 if (!PyLong_Check(obj)) {
652 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
653 "the _handle attribute of the second argument must be an integer");
654 Py_DECREF(obj);
655 return NULL;
656 }
657 handle = (void *)PyLong_AsVoidPtr(obj);
658 Py_DECREF(obj);
659 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
660 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
661 "could not convert the _handle attribute to a pointer");
662 return NULL;
663 }
664
665#ifdef MS_WIN32
666 address = (void *)GetProcAddress(handle, name);
667 if (!address) {
668 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
669 "symbol '%s' not found",
670 name);
671 return NULL;
672 }
673#else
674 address = (void *)ctypes_dlsym(handle, name);
675 if (!address) {
676#ifdef __CYGWIN__
677/* dlerror() isn't very helpful on cygwin */
678 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
679 "symbol '%s' not found",
680 name);
681#else
682 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, ctypes_dlerror());
683#endif
684 return NULL;
685 }
686#endif
687 return PyCData_AtAddress(type, address);
688}

690static const char from_param_doc[] =
691"Convert a Python object into a function call parameter.";
692
693static PyObject *
694CDataType_from_param(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
695{
696 PyObject *as_parameter;
697 int res = PyObject_IsInstance(value, type);
698 if (res == -1)
699 return NULL;
700 if (res) {
701 Py_INCREF(value);
702 return value;
703 }
704 if (PyCArg_CheckExact(value)) {
705 PyCArgObject *p = (PyCArgObject *)value;
706 PyObject *ob = p->obj;
707 const char *ob_name;
708 StgDictObject *dict;
709 dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
710
711 /* If we got a PyCArgObject, we must check if the object packed in it
712 is an instance of the type's dict->proto */
713 if(dict && ob) {
714 res = PyObject_IsInstance(ob, dict->proto);
715 if (res == -1)
716 return NULL;
717 if (res) {
718 Py_INCREF(value);
719 return value;
720 }
721 }
722 ob_name = (ob) ? Py_TYPE(ob)->tp_name : "???";
723 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
724 "expected %s instance instead of pointer to %s",
725 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name, ob_name);
726 return NULL;
727 }
728
729 as_parameter = PyObject_GetAttrString(value, "_as_parameter_");
730 if (as_parameter) {
731 value = CDataType_from_param(type, as_parameter);
732 Py_DECREF(as_parameter);
733 return value;
734 }
735 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
736 "expected %s instance instead of %s",
737 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name,
738 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
739 return NULL;
740}

906/******************************************************************/
907
908/*
909
910The PyCPointerType_Type metaclass must ensure that the subclass of Pointer can be
911created. It must check for a _type_ attribute in the class. Since are no
912runtime created properties, a CField is probably *not* needed ?
913
914class IntPointer(Pointer):
915 _type_ = "i"
916
917The PyCPointer_Type provides the functionality: a contents method/property, a
918size property/method, and the sequence protocol.
919
920*/
921
922static int
923PyCPointerType_SetProto(StgDictObject *stgdict, PyObject *proto)
924{
925 if (!proto || !PyType_Check(proto)) {
926 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
927 "_type_ must be a type");
928 return -1;
929 }
930 if (!PyType_stgdict(proto)) {
931 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
932 "_type_ must have storage info");
933 return -1;
934 }
935 Py_INCREF(proto);
936 Py_XSETREF(stgdict->proto, proto);
937 return 0;
938}
939
940static PyCArgObject *
941PyCPointerType_paramfunc(CDataObject *self)
942{
943 PyCArgObject *parg;
944
945 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
946 if (parg == NULL)
947 return NULL;
948
949 parg->tag = 'P';
950 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
951 Py_INCREF(self);
952 parg->obj = (PyObject *)self;
953 parg->value.p = *(void **)self->b_ptr;
954 return parg;
955}
956
957static PyObject *
958PyCPointerType_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
959{
960 PyTypeObject *result;
961 StgDictObject *stgdict;
962 PyObject *proto;
963 PyObject *typedict;
964
965 typedict = PyTuple_GetItem(args, 2);
966 if (!typedict)
967 return NULL;
968/*
969 stgdict items size, align, length contain info about pointers itself,
970 stgdict->proto has info about the pointed to type!
971*/
972 stgdict = (StgDictObject *)PyObject_CallObject(
973 (PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type, NULL);
974 if (!stgdict)
975 return NULL;
976 stgdict->size = sizeof(void *);
977 stgdict->align = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("P")->pffi_type->alignment;
978 stgdict->length = 1;
979 stgdict->ffi_type_pointer = ffi_type_pointer;
980 stgdict->paramfunc = PyCPointerType_paramfunc;
981 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
982
983 proto = PyDict_GetItemString(typedict, "_type_"); /* Borrowed ref */
984 if (proto && -1 == PyCPointerType_SetProto(stgdict, proto)) {
985 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
986 return NULL;
987 }
988
989 if (proto) {
990 StgDictObject *itemdict = PyType_stgdict(proto);
991 const char *current_format;
992 /* PyCPointerType_SetProto has verified proto has a stgdict. */
993 assert(itemdict);
994 /* If itemdict->format is NULL, then this is a pointer to an
995 incomplete type. We create a generic format string
996 'pointer to bytes' in this case. XXX Better would be to
997 fix the format string later...
998 */
999 current_format = itemdict->format ? itemdict->format : "B";
1000 if (itemdict->shape != NULL) {
1001 /* pointer to an array: the shape needs to be prefixed */
1002 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string_with_shape(
1003 itemdict->ndim, itemdict->shape, "&", current_format);
1004 } else {
1005 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string("&", current_format);
1006 }
1007 if (stgdict->format == NULL) {
1008 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
1009 return NULL;
1010 }
1011 }
1012
1013 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
1014 since we are a metatype!) */
1015 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, args, kwds);
1016 if (result == NULL) {
1017 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
1018 return NULL;
1019 }
1020
1021 /* replace the class dict by our updated spam dict */
1022 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)stgdict, result->tp_dict)) {
1023 Py_DECREF(result);
1024 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
1025 return NULL;
1026 }
1027 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)stgdict);
1028
1029 return (PyObject *)result;
1030}

1032
1033static PyObject *
1034PyCPointerType_set_type(PyTypeObject *self, PyObject *type)
1035{
1036 StgDictObject *dict;
1037
1038 dict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
1039 if (!dict) {
1040 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1041 "abstract class");
1042 return NULL;
1043 }
1044
1045 if (-1 == PyCPointerType_SetProto(dict, type))
1046 return NULL;
1047
1048 if (-1 == PyDict_SetItemString((PyObject *)dict, "_type_", type))
1049 return NULL;
1050
1051 Py_RETURN_NONE;
1052}
1053
1054static PyObject *_byref(PyObject *);
1055
1056static PyObject *
1057PyCPointerType_from_param(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
1058{
1059 StgDictObject *typedict;
1060
1061 if (value == Py_None) {
1062 /* ConvParam will convert to a NULL pointer later */
1063 Py_INCREF(value);
1064 return value;
1065 }
1066
1067 typedict = PyType_stgdict(type);
1068 if (!typedict) {
1069 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1070 "abstract class");
1071 return NULL;
1072 }
1073
1074 /* If we expect POINTER(<type>), but receive a <type> instance, accept
1075 it by calling byref(<type>).
1076 */
1077 switch (PyObject_IsInstance(value, typedict->proto)) {
1078 case 1:
1079 Py_INCREF(value); /* _byref steals a refcount */
1080 return _byref(value);
1081 case -1:
1082 return NULL;
1083 default:
1084 break;
1085 }
1086
1087 if (PointerObject_Check(value) || ArrayObject_Check(value)) {
1088 /* Array instances are also pointers when
1089 the item types are the same.
1090 */
1091 StgDictObject *v = PyObject_stgdict(value);
1092 assert(v); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer or array objects */
1093 if (PyObject_IsSubclass(v->proto, typedict->proto)) {
1094 Py_INCREF(value);
1095 return value;
1096 }
1097 }
1098 return CDataType_from_param(type, value);
1099}

1163static int
1164CharArray_set_raw(CDataObject *self, PyObject *value)
1165{
1166 char *ptr;
1167 Py_ssize_t size;
1168 Py_buffer view;
1169
1170 if (PyObject_GetBuffer(value, &view, PyBUF_SIMPLE) < 0)
1171 return -1;
1172 size = view.len;
1173 ptr = view.buf;
1174 if (size > self->b_size) {
1175 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
1176 "byte string too long");
1177 goto fail;
1178 }
1179
1180 memcpy(self->b_ptr, ptr, size);
1181
1182 PyBuffer_Release(&view);
1183 return 0;
1184 fail:
1185 PyBuffer_Release(&view);
1186 return -1;
1187}
1188
1189static PyObject *
1190CharArray_get_raw(CDataObject *self)
1191{
1192 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(self->b_ptr, self->b_size);
1193}
1194
1195static PyObject *
1196CharArray_get_value(CDataObject *self)
1197{
1198 Py_ssize_t i;
1199 char *ptr = self->b_ptr;
1200 for (i = 0; i < self->b_size; ++i)
1201 if (*ptr++ == '\0')
1202 break;
1203 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(self->b_ptr, i);
1204}
1205
1206static int
1207CharArray_set_value(CDataObject *self, PyObject *value)
1208{
1209 char *ptr;
1210 Py_ssize_t size;
1211
1212 if (value == NULL) {
1213 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1214 "can't delete attribute");
1215 return -1;
1216 }
1217
1218 if (!PyBytes_Check(value)) {
1219 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
1220 "bytes expected instead of %s instance",
1221 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
1222 return -1;
1223 } else
1224 Py_INCREF(value);
1225 size = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(value);
1226 if (size > self->b_size) {
1227 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
1228 "byte string too long");
1229 Py_DECREF(value);
1230 return -1;
1231 }
1232
1233 ptr = PyBytes_AS_STRING(value);
1234 memcpy(self->b_ptr, ptr, size);
1235 if (size < self->b_size)
1236 self->b_ptr[size] = '\0';
1237 Py_DECREF(value);
1238
1239 return 0;
1240}

1252WCharArray_get_value(CDataObject *self)
1253{

1255 wchar_t *ptr = (wchar_t *)self->b_ptr;
1256 for (i = 0; i < self->b_size/(Py_ssize_t)sizeof(wchar_t); ++i)
1257 if (*ptr++ == (wchar_t)0)

1262static int
1263WCharArray_set_value(CDataObject *self, PyObject *value)
1264{
1265 Py_ssize_t result = 0;
1266 Py_UNICODE *wstr;
1267 Py_ssize_t len;
1268
1269 if (value == NULL) {
1270 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1271 "can't delete attribute");
1272 return -1;
1273 }
1274 if (!PyUnicode_Check(value)) {
1275 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
1276 "unicode string expected instead of %s instance",
1277 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
1278 return -1;
1279 } else
1280 Py_INCREF(value);
1281
1282 wstr = PyUnicode_AsUnicodeAndSize(value, &len);
1283 if (wstr == NULL)
1284 return -1;
1285 if ((size_t)len > self->b_size/sizeof(wchar_t)) {
1286 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
1287 "string too long");
1288 result = -1;
1289 goto done;
1290 }
1291 result = PyUnicode_AsWideChar(value,
1292 (wchar_t *)self->b_ptr,
1293 self->b_size/sizeof(wchar_t));
1294 if (result >= 0 && (size_t)result < self->b_size/sizeof(wchar_t))
1295 ((wchar_t *)self->b_ptr)[result] = (wchar_t)0;
1296 done:
1297 Py_DECREF(value);
1298
1299 return result >= 0 ? 0 : -1;
1300}

1385
1386static PyObject *
1387PyCArrayType_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
1388{
1389 PyTypeObject *result;
1390 StgDictObject *stgdict;
1391 StgDictObject *itemdict;
1392 PyObject *length_attr, *type_attr;
1393 long length;
1394 int overflow;
1395 Py_ssize_t itemsize, itemalign;
1396
1397 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
1398 since we are a metatype!) */
1399 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, args, kwds);
1400 if (result == NULL)
1401 return NULL;
1402
1403 /* Initialize these variables to NULL so that we can simplify error
1404 handling by using Py_XDECREF. */
1405 stgdict = NULL;
1406 type_attr = NULL;
1407
1408 length_attr = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "_length_");
1409 if (!length_attr || !PyLong_Check(length_attr)) {
1410 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
1411 "class must define a '_length_' attribute, "
1412 "which must be a positive integer");
1413 Py_XDECREF(length_attr);
1414 goto error;
1415 }
1416 length = PyLong_AsLongAndOverflow(length_attr, &overflow);
1417 if (overflow) {
1418 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
1419 "The '_length_' attribute is too large");
1420 Py_DECREF(length_attr);
1421 goto error;
1422 }
1423 Py_DECREF(length_attr);
1424
1425 type_attr = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "_type_");
1426 if (!type_attr) {
1427 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
1428 "class must define a '_type_' attribute");
1429 goto error;
1430 }
1431
1432 stgdict = (StgDictObject *)PyObject_CallObject(
1433 (PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type, NULL);
1434 if (!stgdict)
1435 goto error;
1436
1437 itemdict = PyType_stgdict(type_attr);
1438 if (!itemdict) {
1439 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1440 "_type_ must have storage info");
1441 goto error;
1442 }
1443
1444 assert(itemdict->format);
1445 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string(NULL, itemdict->format);
1446 if (stgdict->format == NULL)
1447 goto error;
1448 stgdict->ndim = itemdict->ndim + 1;
1449 stgdict->shape = PyMem_Malloc(sizeof(Py_ssize_t) * stgdict->ndim);
1450 if (stgdict->shape == NULL) {
1451 PyErr_NoMemory();
1452 goto error;
1453 }
1454 stgdict->shape[0] = length;
1455 if (stgdict->ndim > 1) {
1456 memmove(&stgdict->shape[1], itemdict->shape,
1457 sizeof(Py_ssize_t) * (stgdict->ndim - 1));
1458 }
1459
1460 itemsize = itemdict->size;
1461 if (length * itemsize < 0) {
1462 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
1463 "array too large");
1464 goto error;
1465 }
1466
1467 itemalign = itemdict->align;
1468
1469 if (itemdict->flags & (TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER | TYPEFLAG_HASPOINTER))
1470 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_HASPOINTER;
1471
1472 stgdict->size = itemsize * length;
1473 stgdict->align = itemalign;
1474 stgdict->length = length;
1475 stgdict->proto = type_attr;
1476
1477 stgdict->paramfunc = &PyCArrayType_paramfunc;
1478
1479 /* Arrays are passed as pointers to function calls. */
1480 stgdict->ffi_type_pointer = ffi_type_pointer;
1481
1482 /* replace the class dict by our updated spam dict */
1483 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)stgdict, result->tp_dict))
1484 goto error;
1485 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)stgdict); /* steal the reference */
1486 stgdict = NULL;
1487
1488 /* Special case for character arrays.
1489 A permanent annoyance: char arrays are also strings!
1490 */
1491 if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("c")->getfunc) {
1492 if (-1 == add_getset(result, CharArray_getsets))
1493 goto error;
1494#ifdef CTYPES_UNICODE
1495 } else if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("u")->getfunc) {
1496 if (-1 == add_getset(result, WCharArray_getsets))
1497 goto error;
1498#endif
1499 }
1500
1501 return (PyObject *)result;
1502error:
1503 Py_XDECREF((PyObject*)stgdict);
1504 Py_XDECREF(type_attr);
1505 Py_DECREF(result);
1506 return NULL;
1507}

1563static const char SIMPLE_TYPE_CHARS[] = "cbBhHiIlLdfuzZqQPXOv?g";
1564
1565static PyObject *
1566c_wchar_p_from_param(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
1567{
1568 PyObject *as_parameter;
1569 int res;
1570 if (value == Py_None) {
1571 Py_RETURN_NONE;
1572 }
1573 if (PyUnicode_Check(value)) {
1574 PyCArgObject *parg;
1575 struct fielddesc *fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("Z");
1576
1577 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1578 if (parg == NULL)
1579 return NULL;
1580 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1581 parg->tag = 'Z';
1582 parg->obj = fd->setfunc(&parg->value, value, 0);
1583 if (parg->obj == NULL) {
1584 Py_DECREF(parg);
1585 return NULL;
1586 }
1587 return (PyObject *)parg;
1588 }
1589 res = PyObject_IsInstance(value, type);
1590 if (res == -1)
1591 return NULL;
1592 if (res) {
1593 Py_INCREF(value);
1594 return value;
1595 }
1596 if (ArrayObject_Check(value) || PointerObject_Check(value)) {
1597 /* c_wchar array instance or pointer(c_wchar(...)) */
1598 StgDictObject *dt = PyObject_stgdict(value);
1599 StgDictObject *dict;
1600 assert(dt); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer or array objects */
1601 dict = dt && dt->proto ? PyType_stgdict(dt->proto) : NULL;
1602 if (dict && (dict->setfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("u")->setfunc)) {
1603 Py_INCREF(value);
1604 return value;
1605 }
1606 }
1607 if (PyCArg_CheckExact(value)) {
1608 /* byref(c_char(...)) */
1609 PyCArgObject *a = (PyCArgObject *)value;
1610 StgDictObject *dict = PyObject_stgdict(a->obj);
1611 if (dict && (dict->setfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("u")->setfunc)) {
1612 Py_INCREF(value);
1613 return value;
1614 }
1615 }
1616
1617 as_parameter = PyObject_GetAttrString(value, "_as_parameter_");
1618 if (as_parameter) {
1619 value = c_wchar_p_from_param(type, as_parameter);
1620 Py_DECREF(as_parameter);
1621 return value;
1622 }
1623 /* XXX better message */
1624 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1625 "wrong type");
1626 return NULL;
1627}

1692
1693static PyObject *
1694c_void_p_from_param(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
1695{
1696 StgDictObject *stgd;
1697 PyObject *as_parameter;
1698 int res;
1699
1700/* None */
1701 if (value == Py_None) {
1702 Py_RETURN_NONE;
1703 }
1704 /* Should probably allow buffer interface as well */
1705/* int, long */
1706 if (PyLong_Check(value)) {
1707 PyCArgObject *parg;
1708 struct fielddesc *fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("P");
1709
1710 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1711 if (parg == NULL)
1712 return NULL;
1713 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1714 parg->tag = 'P';
1715 parg->obj = fd->setfunc(&parg->value, value, 0);
1716 if (parg->obj == NULL) {
1717 Py_DECREF(parg);
1718 return NULL;
1719 }
1720 return (PyObject *)parg;
1721 }
1722 /* XXX struni: remove later */
1723/* bytes */
1724 if (PyBytes_Check(value)) {
1725 PyCArgObject *parg;
1726 struct fielddesc *fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("z");
1727
1728 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1729 if (parg == NULL)
1730 return NULL;
1731 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1732 parg->tag = 'z';
1733 parg->obj = fd->setfunc(&parg->value, value, 0);
1734 if (parg->obj == NULL) {
1735 Py_DECREF(parg);
1736 return NULL;
1737 }
1738 return (PyObject *)parg;
1739 }
1740/* unicode */
1741 if (PyUnicode_Check(value)) {
1742 PyCArgObject *parg;
1743 struct fielddesc *fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("Z");
1744
1745 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1746 if (parg == NULL)
1747 return NULL;
1748 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1749 parg->tag = 'Z';
1750 parg->obj = fd->setfunc(&parg->value, value, 0);
1751 if (parg->obj == NULL) {
1752 Py_DECREF(parg);
1753 return NULL;
1754 }
1755 return (PyObject *)parg;
1756 }
1757/* c_void_p instance (or subclass) */
1758 res = PyObject_IsInstance(value, type);
1759 if (res == -1)
1760 return NULL;
1761 if (res) {
1762 /* c_void_p instances */
1763 Py_INCREF(value);
1764 return value;
1765 }
1766/* ctypes array or pointer instance */
1767 if (ArrayObject_Check(value) || PointerObject_Check(value)) {
1768 /* Any array or pointer is accepted */
1769 Py_INCREF(value);
1770 return value;
1771 }
1772/* byref(...) */
1773 if (PyCArg_CheckExact(value)) {
1774 /* byref(c_xxx()) */
1775 PyCArgObject *a = (PyCArgObject *)value;
1776 if (a->tag == 'P') {
1777 Py_INCREF(value);
1778 return value;
1779 }
1780 }
1781/* function pointer */
1782 if (PyCFuncPtrObject_Check(value)) {
1783 PyCArgObject *parg;
1784 PyCFuncPtrObject *func;
1785 func = (PyCFuncPtrObject *)value;
1786 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1787 if (parg == NULL)
1788 return NULL;
1789 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1790 parg->tag = 'P';
1791 Py_INCREF(value);
1792 parg->value.p = *(void **)func->b_ptr;
1793 parg->obj = value;
1794 return (PyObject *)parg;
1795 }
1796/* c_char_p, c_wchar_p */
1797 stgd = PyObject_stgdict(value);
1798 if (stgd && CDataObject_Check(value) && stgd->proto && PyUnicode_Check(stgd->proto)) {
1799 PyCArgObject *parg;
1800
1801 switch (PyUnicode_AsUTF8(stgd->proto)[0]) {
1802 case 'z': /* c_char_p */
1803 case 'Z': /* c_wchar_p */
1804 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1805 if (parg == NULL)
1806 return NULL;
1807 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
1808 parg->tag = 'Z';
1809 Py_INCREF(value);
1810 parg->obj = value;
1811 /* Remember: b_ptr points to where the pointer is stored! */
1812 parg->value.p = *(void **)(((CDataObject *)value)->b_ptr);
1813 return (PyObject *)parg;
1814 }
1815 }
1816
1817 as_parameter = PyObject_GetAttrString(value, "_as_parameter_");
1818 if (as_parameter) {
1819 value = c_void_p_from_param(type, as_parameter);
1820 Py_DECREF(as_parameter);
1821 return value;
1822 }
1823 /* XXX better message */
1824 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1825 "wrong type");
1826 return NULL;
1827}

1829static PyMethodDef c_void_p_method = { "from_param", c_void_p_from_param, METH_O };
1830static PyMethodDef c_char_p_method = { "from_param", c_char_p_from_param, METH_O };

1833static PyObject *CreateSwappedType(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds,
1834 PyObject *proto, struct fielddesc *fmt)
1835{
1836 PyTypeObject *result;
1837 StgDictObject *stgdict;
1838 PyObject *name = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0);
1839 PyObject *newname;
1840 PyObject *swapped_args;
1841 static PyObject *suffix;
1842 Py_ssize_t i;
1843
1844 swapped_args = PyTuple_New(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args));
1845 if (!swapped_args)
1846 return NULL;
1847
1848 if (suffix == NULL)
1849#ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
1850 suffix = PyUnicode_InternFromString("_le");
1851#else
1852 suffix = PyUnicode_InternFromString("_be");
1853#endif
1854
1855 newname = PyUnicode_Concat(name, suffix);
1856 if (newname == NULL) {
1857 Py_DECREF(swapped_args);
1858 return NULL;
1859 }
1860
1861 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(swapped_args, 0, newname);
1862 for (i=1; i<PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args); ++i) {
1863 PyObject *v = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, i);
1864 Py_INCREF(v);
1865 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(swapped_args, i, v);
1866 }
1867
1868 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
1869 since we are a metatype!) */
1870 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, swapped_args, kwds);
1871 Py_DECREF(swapped_args);
1872 if (result == NULL)
1873 return NULL;
1874
1875 stgdict = (StgDictObject *)PyObject_CallObject(
1876 (PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type, NULL);
1877 if (!stgdict) {
1878 Py_DECREF(result);
1879 return NULL;
1880 }
1881
1882 stgdict->ffi_type_pointer = *fmt->pffi_type;
1883 stgdict->align = fmt->pffi_type->alignment;
1884 stgdict->length = 0;
1885 stgdict->size = fmt->pffi_type->size;
1886 stgdict->setfunc = fmt->setfunc_swapped;
1887 stgdict->getfunc = fmt->getfunc_swapped;
1888
1889 Py_INCREF(proto);
1890 stgdict->proto = proto;
1891
1892 /* replace the class dict by our updated spam dict */
1893 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)stgdict, result->tp_dict)) {
1894 Py_DECREF(result);
1895 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
1896 return NULL;
1897 }
1898 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)stgdict);
1899
1900 return (PyObject *)result;
1901}

1903static PyCArgObject *
1904PyCSimpleType_paramfunc(CDataObject *self)
1905{
1906 StgDictObject *dict;
1907 const char *fmt;
1908 PyCArgObject *parg;
1909 struct fielddesc *fd;
1910
1911 dict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
1912 assert(dict); /* Cannot be NULL for CDataObject instances */
1913 fmt = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(dict->proto);
1914 assert(fmt);
1915
1916 fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc(fmt);
1917 assert(fd);
1918
1919 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
1920 if (parg == NULL)
1921 return NULL;
1922
1923 parg->tag = fmt[0];
1924 parg->pffi_type = fd->pffi_type;
1925 Py_INCREF(self);
1926 parg->obj = (PyObject *)self;
1927 memcpy(&parg->value, self->b_ptr, self->b_size);
1928 return parg;
1929}
1930
1931static PyObject *
1932PyCSimpleType_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
1933{
1934 PyTypeObject *result;
1935 StgDictObject *stgdict;
1936 PyObject *proto;
1937 const char *proto_str;
1938 Py_ssize_t proto_len;
1939 PyMethodDef *ml;
1940 struct fielddesc *fmt;
1941
1942 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
1943 since we are a metatype!) */
1944 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, args, kwds);
1945 if (result == NULL)
1946 return NULL;
1947
1948 proto = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "_type_"); /* new ref */
1949 if (!proto) {
1950 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
1951 "class must define a '_type_' attribute");
1952 error:
1953 Py_XDECREF(proto);
1954 Py_XDECREF(result);
1955 return NULL;
1956 }
1957 if (PyUnicode_Check(proto)) {
1958 proto_str = PyUnicode_AsUTF8AndSize(proto, &proto_len);
1959 if (!proto_str)
1960 goto error;
1961 } else {
1962 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1963 "class must define a '_type_' string attribute");
1964 goto error;
1965 }
1966 if (proto_len != 1) {
1967 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
1968 "class must define a '_type_' attribute "
1969 "which must be a string of length 1");
1970 goto error;
1971 }
1972 if (!strchr(SIMPLE_TYPE_CHARS, *proto_str)) {
1973 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
1974 "class must define a '_type_' attribute which must be\n"
1975 "a single character string containing one of '%s'.",
1976 SIMPLE_TYPE_CHARS);
1977 goto error;
1978 }
1979 fmt = _ctypes_get_fielddesc(proto_str);
1980 if (fmt == NULL) {
1981 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
1982 "_type_ '%s' not supported", proto_str);
1983 goto error;
1984 }
1985
1986 stgdict = (StgDictObject *)PyObject_CallObject(
1987 (PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type, NULL);
1988 if (!stgdict)
1989 goto error;
1990
1991 stgdict->ffi_type_pointer = *fmt->pffi_type;
1992 stgdict->align = fmt->pffi_type->alignment;
1993 stgdict->length = 0;
1994 stgdict->size = fmt->pffi_type->size;
1995 stgdict->setfunc = fmt->setfunc;
1996 stgdict->getfunc = fmt->getfunc;
1997#ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
1998 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string_for_type(proto_str[0], 1);
1999#else
2000 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string_for_type(proto_str[0], 0);
2001#endif
2002 if (stgdict->format == NULL) {
2003 Py_DECREF(result);
2004 Py_DECREF(proto);
2005 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
2006 return NULL;
2007 }
2008
2009 stgdict->paramfunc = PyCSimpleType_paramfunc;
2010/*
2011 if (result->tp_base != &Simple_Type) {
2012 stgdict->setfunc = NULL;
2013 stgdict->getfunc = NULL;
2014 }
2015*/
2016
2017 /* This consumes the refcount on proto which we have */
2018 stgdict->proto = proto;
2019
2020 /* replace the class dict by our updated spam dict */
2021 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)stgdict, result->tp_dict)) {
2022 Py_DECREF(result);
2023 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
2024 return NULL;
2025 }
2026 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)stgdict);
2027
2028 /* Install from_param class methods in ctypes base classes.
2029 Overrides the PyCSimpleType_from_param generic method.
2030 */
2031 if (result->tp_base == &Simple_Type) {
2032 switch (*proto_str) {
2033 case 'z': /* c_char_p */
2034 ml = &c_char_p_method;
2035 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2036 break;
2037 case 'Z': /* c_wchar_p */
2038 ml = &c_wchar_p_method;
2039 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2040 break;
2041 case 'P': /* c_void_p */
2042 ml = &c_void_p_method;
2043 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2044 break;
2045 case 's':
2046 case 'X':
2047 case 'O':
2048 ml = NULL;
2049 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2050 break;
2051 default:
2052 ml = NULL;
2053 break;
2054 }
2055
2056 if (ml) {
2057 PyObject *meth;
2058 int x;
2059 meth = PyDescr_NewClassMethod(result, ml);
2060 if (!meth) {
2061 Py_DECREF(result);
2062 return NULL;
2063 }
2064 x = PyDict_SetItemString(result->tp_dict,
2065 ml->ml_name,
2066 meth);
2067 Py_DECREF(meth);
2068 if (x == -1) {
2069 Py_DECREF(result);
2070 return NULL;
2071 }
2072 }
2073 }
2074
2075 if (type == &PyCSimpleType_Type && fmt->setfunc_swapped && fmt->getfunc_swapped) {
2076 PyObject *swapped = CreateSwappedType(type, args, kwds,
2077 proto, fmt);
2078 StgDictObject *sw_dict;
2079 if (swapped == NULL) {
2080 Py_DECREF(result);
2081 return NULL;
2082 }
2083 sw_dict = PyType_stgdict(swapped);
2084#ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
2085 PyObject_SetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "__ctype_le__", swapped);
2086 PyObject_SetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "__ctype_be__", (PyObject *)result);
2087 PyObject_SetAttrString(swapped, "__ctype_be__", (PyObject *)result);
2088 PyObject_SetAttrString(swapped, "__ctype_le__", swapped);
2089 /* We are creating the type for the OTHER endian */
2090 sw_dict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string("<", stgdict->format+1);
2091#else
2092 PyObject_SetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "__ctype_be__", swapped);
2093 PyObject_SetAttrString((PyObject *)result, "__ctype_le__", (PyObject *)result);
2094 PyObject_SetAttrString(swapped, "__ctype_le__", (PyObject *)result);
2095 PyObject_SetAttrString(swapped, "__ctype_be__", swapped);
2096 /* We are creating the type for the OTHER endian */
2097 sw_dict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string(">", stgdict->format+1);
2098#endif
2099 Py_DECREF(swapped);
2100 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
2101 Py_DECREF(result);
2102 return NULL;
2103 }
2104 };
2105
2106 return (PyObject *)result;
2107}

2109/*
2110 * This is a *class method*.
2111 * Convert a parameter into something that ConvParam can handle.
2112 */
2113static PyObject *
2114PyCSimpleType_from_param(PyObject *type, PyObject *value)
2115{
2116 StgDictObject *dict;
2117 const char *fmt;
2118 PyCArgObject *parg;
2119 struct fielddesc *fd;
2120 PyObject *as_parameter;
2121 int res;
2122
2123 /* If the value is already an instance of the requested type,
2124 we can use it as is */
2125 res = PyObject_IsInstance(value, type);
2126 if (res == -1)
2127 return NULL;
2128 if (res) {
2129 Py_INCREF(value);
2130 return value;
2131 }
2132
2133 dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
2134 if (!dict) {
2135 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2136 "abstract class");
2137 return NULL;
2138 }
2139
2140 /* I think we can rely on this being a one-character string */
2141 fmt = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(dict->proto);
2142 assert(fmt);
2143
2144 fd = _ctypes_get_fielddesc(fmt);
2145 assert(fd);
2146
2147 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
2148 if (parg == NULL)
2149 return NULL;
2150
2151 parg->tag = fmt[0];
2152 parg->pffi_type = fd->pffi_type;
2153 parg->obj = fd->setfunc(&parg->value, value, 0);
2154 if (parg->obj)
2155 return (PyObject *)parg;
2156 PyErr_Clear();
2157 Py_DECREF(parg);
2158
2159 as_parameter = PyObject_GetAttrString(value, "_as_parameter_");
2160 if (as_parameter) {
2161 if (Py_EnterRecursiveCall("while processing _as_parameter_")) {
2162 Py_DECREF(as_parameter);
2163 return NULL;
2164 }
2165 value = PyCSimpleType_from_param(type, as_parameter);
2166 Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
2167 Py_DECREF(as_parameter);
2168 return value;
2169 }
2170 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2171 "wrong type");
2172 return NULL;
2173}

2227/*
2228 PyCFuncPtrType_Type
2229 */
2230
2231static PyObject *
2232converters_from_argtypes(PyObject *ob)
2233{
2234 PyObject *converters;
2235 Py_ssize_t i;
2236 Py_ssize_t nArgs;
2237
2238 ob = PySequence_Tuple(ob); /* new reference */
2239 if (!ob) {
2240 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2241 "_argtypes_ must be a sequence of types");
2242 return NULL;
2243 }
2244
2245 nArgs = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(ob);
2246 converters = PyTuple_New(nArgs);
2247 if (!converters) {
2248 Py_DECREF(ob);
2249 return NULL;
2250 }
2251
2252 /* I have to check if this is correct. Using c_char, which has a size
2253 of 1, will be assumed to be pushed as only one byte!
2254 Aren't these promoted to integers by the C compiler and pushed as 4 bytes?
2255 */
2256
2257 for (i = 0; i < nArgs; ++i) {
2258 PyObject *tp = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(ob, i);
2259 PyObject *cnv = PyObject_GetAttrString(tp, "from_param");
2260 if (!cnv)
2261 goto argtypes_error_1;
2262 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(converters, i, cnv);
2263 }
2264 Py_DECREF(ob);
2265 return converters;
2266
2267 argtypes_error_1:
2268 Py_XDECREF(converters);
2269 Py_DECREF(ob);
2270 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
2271 "item %zd in _argtypes_ has no from_param method",
2272 i+1);
2273 return NULL;
2274}
2275
2276static int
2277make_funcptrtype_dict(StgDictObject *stgdict)
2278{
2279 PyObject *ob;
2280 PyObject *converters = NULL;
2281
2282 stgdict->align = _ctypes_get_fielddesc("P")->pffi_type->alignment;
2283 stgdict->length = 1;
2284 stgdict->size = sizeof(void *);
2285 stgdict->setfunc = NULL;
2286 stgdict->getfunc = NULL;
2287 stgdict->ffi_type_pointer = ffi_type_pointer;
2288
2289 ob = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)stgdict, "_flags_");
2290 if (!ob || !PyLong_Check(ob)) {
2291 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2292 "class must define _flags_ which must be an integer");
2293 return -1;
2294 }
2295 stgdict->flags = PyLong_AS_LONG(ob) | TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2296
2297 /* _argtypes_ is optional... */
2298 ob = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)stgdict, "_argtypes_");
2299 if (ob) {
2300 converters = converters_from_argtypes(ob);
2301 if (!converters)
2302 goto error;
2303 Py_INCREF(ob);
2304 stgdict->argtypes = ob;
2305 stgdict->converters = converters;
2306 }
2307
2308 ob = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)stgdict, "_restype_");
2309 if (ob) {
2310 if (ob != Py_None && !PyType_stgdict(ob) && !PyCallable_Check(ob)) {
2311 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2312 "_restype_ must be a type, a callable, or None");
2313 return -1;
2314 }
2315 Py_INCREF(ob);
2316 stgdict->restype = ob;
2317 stgdict->checker = PyObject_GetAttrString(ob, "_check_retval_");
2318 if (stgdict->checker == NULL)
2319 PyErr_Clear();
2320 }
2321/* XXX later, maybe.
2322 ob = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)stgdict, "_errcheck_");
2323 if (ob) {
2324 if (!PyCallable_Check(ob)) {
2325 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2326 "_errcheck_ must be callable");
2327 return -1;
2328 }
2329 Py_INCREF(ob);
2330 stgdict->errcheck = ob;
2331 }
2332*/
2333 return 0;
2334
2335 error:
2336 Py_XDECREF(converters);
2337 return -1;
2338
2339}

2347 if (parg == NULL)

2358static PyObject *
2359PyCFuncPtrType_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
2360{
2361 PyTypeObject *result;
2362 StgDictObject *stgdict;
2363
2364 stgdict = (StgDictObject *)PyObject_CallObject(
2365 (PyObject *)&PyCStgDict_Type, NULL);
2366 if (!stgdict)
2367 return NULL;
2368
2369 stgdict->paramfunc = PyCFuncPtrType_paramfunc;
2370 /* We do NOT expose the function signature in the format string. It
2371 is impossible, generally, because the only requirement for the
2372 argtypes items is that they have a .from_param method - we do not
2373 know the types of the arguments (although, in practice, most
2374 argtypes would be a ctypes type).
2375 */
2376 stgdict->format = _ctypes_alloc_format_string(NULL, "X{}");
2377 if (stgdict->format == NULL) {
2378 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
2379 return NULL;
2380 }
2381 stgdict->flags |= TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER;
2382
2383 /* create the new instance (which is a class,
2384 since we are a metatype!) */
2385 result = (PyTypeObject *)PyType_Type.tp_new(type, args, kwds);
2386 if (result == NULL) {
2387 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
2388 return NULL;
2389 }
2390
2391 /* replace the class dict by our updated storage dict */
2392 if (-1 == PyDict_Update((PyObject *)stgdict, result->tp_dict)) {
2393 Py_DECREF(result);
2394 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)stgdict);
2395 return NULL;
2396 }
2397 Py_SETREF(result->tp_dict, (PyObject *)stgdict);
2398
2399 if (-1 == make_funcptrtype_dict(stgdict)) {
2400 Py_DECREF(result);
2401 return NULL;
2402 }
2403
2404 return (PyObject *)result;
2405}

2451 * Code to keep needed objects alive

2453
2454static CDataObject *
2455PyCData_GetContainer(CDataObject *self)
2456{
2457 while (self->b_base)
2458 self = self->b_base;
2459 if (self->b_objects == NULL) {
2460 if (self->b_length) {
2461 self->b_objects = PyDict_New();
2462 if (self->b_objects == NULL)
2463 return NULL;
2464 } else {
2465 Py_INCREF(Py_None);
2466 self->b_objects = Py_None;
2467 }
2468 }
2469 return self;
2470}

2473GetKeepedObjects(CDataObject *target)
2474{

2476 container = PyCData_GetContainer(target);
2477 if (container == NULL)

2481
2482static PyObject *
2483unique_key(CDataObject *target, Py_ssize_t index)
2484{
2485 char string[256];
2486 char *cp = string;
2487 size_t bytes_left;
2488
2489 Py_BUILD_ASSERT(sizeof(string) - 1 > sizeof(Py_ssize_t) * 2);
2490 cp += sprintf(cp, "%x", Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(index, Py_ssize_t, int));
2491 while (target->b_base) {
2492 bytes_left = sizeof(string) - (cp - string) - 1;
2493 /* Hex format needs 2 characters per byte */
2494 if (bytes_left < sizeof(Py_ssize_t) * 2) {
2495 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
2496 "ctypes object structure too deep");
2497 return NULL;
2498 }
2499 cp += sprintf(cp, ":%x", Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(target->b_index, Py_ssize_t, int));
2500 target = target->b_base;
2501 }
2502 return PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(string, cp-string);
2503}
2504
2505/*
2506 * Keep a reference to 'keep' in the 'target', at index 'index'.
2507 *
2508 * If 'keep' is None, do nothing.
2509 *
2510 * Otherwise create a dictionary (if it does not yet exist) id the root
2511 * objects 'b_objects' item, which will store the 'keep' object under a unique
2512 * key.
2513 *
2514 * The unique_key helper travels the target's b_base pointer down to the root,
2515 * building a string containing hex-formatted indexes found during traversal,
2516 * separated by colons.
2517 *
2518 * The index tuple is used as a key into the root object's b_objects dict.
2519 *
2520 * Note: This function steals a refcount of the third argument, even if it
2521 * fails!
2522 */
2523static int
2524KeepRef(CDataObject *target, Py_ssize_t index, PyObject *keep)
2525{
2526 int result;
2527 CDataObject *ob;
2528 PyObject *key;
2529
2530/* Optimization: no need to store None */
2531 if (keep == Py_None) {
2532 Py_DECREF(Py_None);
2533 return 0;
2534 }
2535 ob = PyCData_GetContainer(target);
2536 if (ob == NULL) {
2537 Py_DECREF(keep);
2538 return -1;
2539 }
2540 if (ob->b_objects == NULL || !PyDict_CheckExact(ob->b_objects)) {
2541 Py_XSETREF(ob->b_objects, keep); /* refcount consumed */
2542 return 0;
2543 }
2544 key = unique_key(target, index);
2545 if (key == NULL) {
2546 Py_DECREF(keep);
2547 return -1;
2548 }
2549 result = PyDict_SetItem(ob->b_objects, key, keep);
2550 Py_DECREF(key);
2551 Py_DECREF(keep);
2552 return result;
2553}

2600{
2601 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
2602 StgDictObject *dict = PyObject_stgdict(myself);
2603 Py_ssize_t i;
2604
2605 if (view == NULL) return 0;
2606
2607 view->buf = self->b_ptr;
2608 view->obj = myself;
2609 Py_INCREF(myself);
2610 view->len = self->b_size;

2618 for (i = 0; i < view->ndim; ++i) {
2619 view->itemsize /= dict->shape[i];
2620 }
2621 }
2622 view->strides = NULL;
2623 view->suboffsets = NULL;
2624 view->internal = NULL;

2643static PyObject *
2644PyCData_reduce(PyObject *myself, PyObject *args)
2645{
2646 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
2647
2648 if (PyObject_stgdict(myself)->flags & (TYPEFLAG_ISPOINTER|TYPEFLAG_HASPOINTER)) {
2649 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
2650 "ctypes objects containing pointers cannot be pickled");
2651 return NULL;
2652 }
2653 return Py_BuildValue("O(O(NN))",
2654 _unpickle,

2657 PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(self->b_ptr, self->b_size));

2660static PyObject *
2661PyCData_setstate(PyObject *myself, PyObject *args)
2662{
2663 void *data;
2664 Py_ssize_t len;
2665 int res;
2666 PyObject *dict, *mydict;
2667 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
2668 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "Os#", &dict, &data, &len))
2669 return NULL;
2670 if (len > self->b_size)
2671 len = self->b_size;
2672 memmove(self->b_ptr, data, len);
2673 mydict = PyObject_GetAttrString(myself, "__dict__");
2674 res = PyDict_Update(mydict, dict);
2675 Py_DECREF(mydict);
2676 if (res == -1)
2677 return NULL;
2678 Py_RETURN_NONE;
2679}

2740static int PyCData_MallocBuffer(CDataObject *obj, StgDictObject *dict)
2741{
2742 if ((size_t)dict->size <= sizeof(obj->b_value)) {
2743 /* No need to call malloc, can use the default buffer */
2744 obj->b_ptr = (char *)&obj->b_value;
2745 /* The b_needsfree flag does not mean that we actually did
2746 call PyMem_Malloc to allocate the memory block; instead it
2747 means we are the *owner* of the memory and are responsible
2748 for freeing resources associated with the memory. This is
2749 also the reason that b_needsfree is exposed to Python.
2750 */
2751 obj->b_needsfree = 1;
2752 } else {
2753 /* In python 2.4, and ctypes 0.9.6, the malloc call took about
2754 33% of the creation time for c_int().
2755 */
2756 obj->b_ptr = (char *)PyMem_Malloc(dict->size);
2757 if (obj->b_ptr == NULL) {
2758 PyErr_NoMemory();
2759 return -1;
2760 }
2761 obj->b_needsfree = 1;
2762 memset(obj->b_ptr, 0, dict->size);
2763 }
2764 obj->b_size = dict->size;
2765 return 0;
2766}
2767
2768PyObject *
2769PyCData_FromBaseObj(PyObject *type, PyObject *base, Py_ssize_t index, char *adr)
2770{
2771 CDataObject *cmem;
2772 StgDictObject *dict;
2773
2774 assert(PyType_Check(type));
2775 dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
2776 if (!dict) {
2777 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2778 "abstract class");
2779 return NULL;
2780 }
2781 dict->flags |= DICTFLAG_FINAL;
2782 cmem = (CDataObject *)((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_alloc((PyTypeObject *)type, 0);
2783 if (cmem == NULL)
2784 return NULL;
2785 assert(CDataObject_Check(cmem));
2786
2787 cmem->b_length = dict->length;
2788 cmem->b_size = dict->size;
2789 if (base) { /* use base's buffer */
2790 assert(CDataObject_Check(base));
2791 cmem->b_ptr = adr;
2792 cmem->b_needsfree = 0;
2793 Py_INCREF(base);
2794 cmem->b_base = (CDataObject *)base;
2795 cmem->b_index = index;
2796 } else { /* copy contents of adr */
2797 if (-1 == PyCData_MallocBuffer(cmem, dict)) {
2798 Py_DECREF(cmem);
2799 return NULL;
2800 }
2801 memcpy(cmem->b_ptr, adr, dict->size);
2802 cmem->b_index = index;
2803 }
2804 return (PyObject *)cmem;
2805}

2863/*
2864 Helper function for PyCData_set below.
2865*/
2866static PyObject *
2867_PyCData_set(CDataObject *dst, PyObject *type, SETFUNC setfunc, PyObject *value,
2868 Py_ssize_t size, char *ptr)
2869{
2870 CDataObject *src;
2871 int err;
2872
2873 if (setfunc)
2874 return setfunc(ptr, value, size);
2875
2876 if (!CDataObject_Check(value)) {
2877 StgDictObject *dict = PyType_stgdict(type);
2878 if (dict && dict->setfunc)
2879 return dict->setfunc(ptr, value, size);
2880 /*
2881 If value is a tuple, we try to call the type with the tuple
2882 and use the result!
2883 */
2884 assert(PyType_Check(type));
2885 if (PyTuple_Check(value)) {
2886 PyObject *ob;
2887 PyObject *result;
2888 ob = PyObject_CallObject(type, value);
2889 if (ob == NULL) {
2890 _ctypes_extend_error(PyExc_RuntimeError, "(%s) ",
2891 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name);
2892 return NULL;
2893 }
2894 result = _PyCData_set(dst, type, setfunc, ob,
2895 size, ptr);
2896 Py_DECREF(ob);
2897 return result;
2898 } else if (value == Py_None && PyCPointerTypeObject_Check(type)) {
2899 *(void **)ptr = NULL;
2900 Py_RETURN_NONE;
2901 } else {
2902 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
2903 "expected %s instance, got %s",
2904 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name,
2905 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
2906 return NULL;
2907 }
2908 }
2909 src = (CDataObject *)value;
2910
2911 err = PyObject_IsInstance(value, type);
2912 if (err == -1)
2913 return NULL;
2914 if (err) {
2915 memcpy(ptr,
2916 src->b_ptr,
2917 size);
2918
2919 if (PyCPointerTypeObject_Check(type)) {
2920 /* XXX */
2921 }
2922
2923 value = GetKeepedObjects(src);
2924 if (value == NULL)
2925 return NULL;
2926
2927 Py_INCREF(value);
2928 return value;
2929 }
2930
2931 if (PyCPointerTypeObject_Check(type)
2932 && ArrayObject_Check(value)) {
2933 StgDictObject *p1, *p2;
2934 PyObject *keep;
2935 p1 = PyObject_stgdict(value);
2936 assert(p1); /* Cannot be NULL for array instances */
2937 p2 = PyType_stgdict(type);
2938 assert(p2); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer types */
2939
2940 if (p1->proto != p2->proto) {
2941 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
2942 "incompatible types, %s instance instead of %s instance",
2943 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name,
2944 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name);
2945 return NULL;
2946 }
2947 *(void **)ptr = src->b_ptr;
2948
2949 keep = GetKeepedObjects(src);
2950 if (keep == NULL)
2951 return NULL;
2952
2953 /*
2954 We are assigning an array object to a field which represents
2955 a pointer. This has the same effect as converting an array
2956 into a pointer. So, again, we have to keep the whole object
2957 pointed to (which is the array in this case) alive, and not
2958 only it's object list. So we create a tuple, containing
2959 b_objects list PLUS the array itself, and return that!
2960 */
2961 return PyTuple_Pack(2, keep, value);
2962 }
2963 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
2964 "incompatible types, %s instance instead of %s instance",
2965 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name,
2966 ((PyTypeObject *)type)->tp_name);
2967 return NULL;
2968}

2970/*
2971 * Set a slice in object 'dst', which has the type 'type',
2972 * to the value 'value'.
2973 */
2974int
2975PyCData_set(PyObject *dst, PyObject *type, SETFUNC setfunc, PyObject *value,
2976 Py_ssize_t index, Py_ssize_t size, char *ptr)
2977{
2978 CDataObject *mem = (CDataObject *)dst;
2979 PyObject *result;
2980
2981 if (!CDataObject_Check(dst)) {
2982 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2983 "not a ctype instance");
2984 return -1;
2985 }
2986
2987 result = _PyCData_set(mem, type, setfunc, value,
2988 size, ptr);
2989 if (result == NULL)
2990 return -1;
2991
2992 /* KeepRef steals a refcount from it's last argument */
2993 /* If KeepRef fails, we are stumped. The dst memory block has already
2994 been changed */
2995 return KeepRef(mem, index, result);
2996}

3144#ifdef MS_WIN32
3145static PPROC FindAddress(void *handle, const char *name, PyObject *type)
3146{
3147#ifdef MS_WIN64
3148 /* win64 has no stdcall calling conv, so it should
3149 also not have the name mangling of it.
3150 */
3151 return (PPROC)GetProcAddress(handle, name);
3152#else
3153 PPROC address;
3154 char *mangled_name;
3155 int i;
3156 StgDictObject *dict;
3157
3158 address = (PPROC)GetProcAddress(handle, name);
3159 if (address)
3160 return address;
3161 if (((size_t)name & ~0xFFFF) == 0) {
3162 return NULL;
3163 }
3164
3165 dict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)type);
3166 /* It should not happen that dict is NULL, but better be safe */
3167 if (dict==NULL || dict->flags & FUNCFLAG_CDECL)
3168 return address;
3169
3170 /* for stdcall, try mangled names:
3171 funcname -> _funcname@<n>
3172 where n is 0, 4, 8, 12, ..., 128
3173 */
3174 mangled_name = alloca(strlen(name) + 1 + 1 + 1 + 3); /* \0 _ @ %d */
3175 if (!mangled_name)
3176 return NULL;
3177 for (i = 0; i < 32; ++i) {
3178 sprintf(mangled_name, "_%s@%d", name, i*4);
3179 address = (PPROC)GetProcAddress(handle, mangled_name);
3180 if (address)
3181 return address;
3182 }
3183 return NULL;
3184#endif
3185}
3186#endif

3188/* Return 1 if usable, 0 else and exception set. */
3189static int
3190_check_outarg_type(PyObject *arg, Py_ssize_t index)
3191{
3192 StgDictObject *dict;
3193
3194 if (PyCPointerTypeObject_Check(arg))
3195 return 1;
3196
3197 if (PyCArrayTypeObject_Check(arg))
3198 return 1;
3199
3200 dict = PyType_stgdict(arg);
3201 if (dict
3202 /* simple pointer types, c_void_p, c_wchar_p, BSTR, ... */
3203 && PyUnicode_Check(dict->proto)
3204/* We only allow c_void_p, c_char_p and c_wchar_p as a simple output parameter type */
3205 && (strchr("PzZ", PyUnicode_AsUTF8(dict->proto)[0]))) {
3206 return 1;
3207 }
3208
3209 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3210 "'out' parameter %d must be a pointer type, not %s",
3211 Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(index, Py_ssize_t, int),
3212 PyType_Check(arg) ?
3213 ((PyTypeObject *)arg)->tp_name :
3214 Py_TYPE(arg)->tp_name);
3215 return 0;
3216}
3217
3218/* Returns 1 on success, 0 on error */
3219static int
3220_validate_paramflags(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *paramflags)
3221{
3222 Py_ssize_t i, len;
3223 StgDictObject *dict;
3224 PyObject *argtypes;
3225
3226 dict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)type);
3227 if (!dict) {
3228 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3229 "abstract class");
3230 return 0;
3231 }
3232 argtypes = dict->argtypes;
3233
3234 if (paramflags == NULL || dict->argtypes == NULL)
3235 return 1;
3236
3237 if (!PyTuple_Check(paramflags)) {
3238 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3239 "paramflags must be a tuple or None");
3240 return 0;
3241 }
3242
3243 len = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(paramflags);
3244 if (len != PyTuple_GET_SIZE(dict->argtypes)) {
3245 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
3246 "paramflags must have the same length as argtypes");
3247 return 0;
3248 }
3249
3250 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
3251 PyObject *item = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(paramflags, i);
3252 int flag;
3253 char *name;
3254 PyObject *defval;
3255 PyObject *typ;
3256 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(item, "i|ZO", &flag, &name, &defval)) {
3257 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3258 "paramflags must be a sequence of (int [,string [,value]]) tuples");
3259 return 0;
3260 }
3261 typ = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argtypes, i);
3262 switch (flag & (PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FOUT | PARAMFLAG_FLCID)) {
3263 case 0:
3264 case PARAMFLAG_FIN:
3265 case PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FLCID:
3266 case PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FOUT:
3267 break;
3268 case PARAMFLAG_FOUT:
3269 if (!_check_outarg_type(typ, i+1))
3270 return 0;
3271 break;
3272 default:
3273 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3274 "paramflag value %d not supported",
3275 flag);
3276 return 0;
3277 }
3278 }
3279 return 1;
3280}

3282static int
3283_get_name(PyObject *obj, const char **pname)
3284{
3285#ifdef MS_WIN32
3286 if (PyLong_Check(obj)) {
3287 /* We have to use MAKEINTRESOURCEA for Windows CE.
3288 Works on Windows as well, of course.
3289 */
3290 *pname = MAKEINTRESOURCEA(PyLong_AsUnsignedLongMask(obj) & 0xFFFF);
3291 return 1;
3292 }
3293#endif
3294 if (PyBytes_Check(obj)) {
3295 *pname = PyBytes_AS_STRING(obj);
3296 return *pname ? 1 : 0;
3297 }
3298 if (PyUnicode_Check(obj)) {
3299 *pname = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(obj);
3300 return *pname ? 1 : 0;
3301 }
3302 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3303 "function name must be string, bytes object or integer");
3304 return 0;
3305}

3308static PyObject *
3309PyCFuncPtr_FromDll(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
3310{
3311 const char *name;
3312 int (* address)(void);
3313 PyObject *ftuple;
3314 PyObject *dll;
3315 PyObject *obj;
3316 PyCFuncPtrObject *self;
3317 void *handle;
3318 PyObject *paramflags = NULL;
3319
3320 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O|O", &ftuple, &paramflags))
3321 return NULL;
3322 if (paramflags == Py_None)
3323 paramflags = NULL;
3324
3325 ftuple = PySequence_Tuple(ftuple);
3326 if (!ftuple)
3327 /* Here ftuple is a borrowed reference */
3328 return NULL;
3329
3330 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(ftuple, "O&O;illegal func_spec argument",
3331 _get_name, &name, &dll))
3332 {
3333 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3334 return NULL;
3335 }
3336
3337 obj = PyObject_GetAttrString(dll, "_handle");
3338 if (!obj) {
3339 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3340 return NULL;
3341 }
3342 if (!PyLong_Check(obj)) {
3343 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3344 "the _handle attribute of the second argument must be an integer");
3345 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3346 Py_DECREF(obj);
3347 return NULL;
3348 }
3349 handle = (void *)PyLong_AsVoidPtr(obj);
3350 Py_DECREF(obj);
3351 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
3352 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
3353 "could not convert the _handle attribute to a pointer");
3354 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3355 return NULL;
3356 }
3357
3358#ifdef MS_WIN32
3359 address = FindAddress(handle, name, (PyObject *)type);
3360 if (!address) {
3361 if (!IS_INTRESOURCE(name))
3362 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
3363 "function '%s' not found",
3364 name);
3365 else
3366 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
3367 "function ordinal %d not found",
3368 (WORD)(size_t)name);
3369 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3370 return NULL;
3371 }
3372#else
3373 address = (PPROC)ctypes_dlsym(handle, name);
3374 if (!address) {
3375#ifdef __CYGWIN__
3376/* dlerror() isn't very helpful on cygwin */
3377 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
3378 "function '%s' not found",
3379 name);
3380#else
3381 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, ctypes_dlerror());
3382#endif
3383 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3384 return NULL;
3385 }
3386#endif
3387 Py_INCREF(dll); /* for KeepRef */
3388 Py_DECREF(ftuple);
3389 if (!_validate_paramflags(type, paramflags))
3390 return NULL;
3391
3392 self = (PyCFuncPtrObject *)GenericPyCData_new(type, args, kwds);
3393 if (!self)
3394 return NULL;
3395
3396 Py_XINCREF(paramflags);
3397 self->paramflags = paramflags;
3398
3399 *(void **)self->b_ptr = address;
3400
3401 if (-1 == KeepRef((CDataObject *)self, 0, dll)) {
3402 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)self);
3403 return NULL;
3404 }
3405
3406 Py_INCREF(self);
3407 self->callable = (PyObject *)self;
3408 return (PyObject *)self;
3409}

3440/*
3441 PyCFuncPtr_new accepts different argument lists in addition to the standard
3442 _basespec_ keyword arg:
3443
3444 one argument form
3445 "i" - function address
3446 "O" - must be a callable, creates a C callable function
3447
3448 two or more argument forms (the third argument is a paramflags tuple)
3449 "(sO)|..." - (function name, dll object (with an integer handle)), paramflags
3450 "(iO)|..." - (function ordinal, dll object (with an integer handle)), paramflags
3451 "is|..." - vtable index, method name, creates callable calling COM vtbl
3452*/
3453static PyObject *
3454PyCFuncPtr_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
3455{
3456 PyCFuncPtrObject *self;
3457 PyObject *callable;
3458 StgDictObject *dict;
3459 CThunkObject *thunk;
3460
3461 if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args) == 0)
3462 return GenericPyCData_new(type, args, kwds);
3463
3464 if (1 <= PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args) && PyTuple_Check(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0)))
3465 return PyCFuncPtr_FromDll(type, args, kwds);
3466
3467#ifdef MS_WIN32
3468 if (2 <= PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args) && PyLong_Check(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0)))
3469 return PyCFuncPtr_FromVtblIndex(type, args, kwds);
3470#endif
3471
3472 if (1 == PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args)
3473 && (PyLong_Check(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0)))) {
3474 CDataObject *ob;
3475 void *ptr = PyLong_AsVoidPtr(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0));
3476 if (ptr == NULL && PyErr_Occurred())
3477 return NULL;
3478 ob = (CDataObject *)GenericPyCData_new(type, args, kwds);
3479 if (ob == NULL)
3480 return NULL;
3481 *(void **)ob->b_ptr = ptr;
3482 return (PyObject *)ob;
3483 }
3484
3485 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O", &callable))
3486 return NULL;
3487 if (!PyCallable_Check(callable)) {
3488 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3489 "argument must be callable or integer function address");
3490 return NULL;
3491 }
3492
3493 /* XXX XXX This would allow passing additional options. For COM
3494 method *implementations*, we would probably want different
3495 behaviour than in 'normal' callback functions: return a HRESULT if
3496 an exception occurs in the callback, and print the traceback not
3497 only on the console, but also to OutputDebugString() or something
3498 like that.
3499 */
3500/*
3501 if (kwds && PyDict_GetItemString(kwds, "options")) {
3502 ...
3503 }
3504*/
3505
3506 dict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)type);
3507 /* XXXX Fails if we do: 'PyCFuncPtr(lambda x: x)' */
3508 if (!dict || !dict->argtypes) {
3509 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3510 "cannot construct instance of this class:"
3511 " no argtypes");
3512 return NULL;
3513 }
3514
3515 thunk = _ctypes_alloc_callback(callable,
3516 dict->argtypes,
3517 dict->restype,
3518 dict->flags);
3519 if (!thunk)
3520 return NULL;
3521
3522 self = (PyCFuncPtrObject *)GenericPyCData_new(type, args, kwds);
3523 if (self == NULL) {
3524 Py_DECREF(thunk);
3525 return NULL;
3526 }
3527
3528 Py_INCREF(callable);
3529 self->callable = callable;
3530
3531 self->thunk = thunk;
3532 *(void **)self->b_ptr = (void *)thunk->pcl_exec;
3533
3534 Py_INCREF((PyObject *)thunk); /* for KeepRef */
3535 if (-1 == KeepRef((CDataObject *)self, 0, (PyObject *)thunk)) {
3536 Py_DECREF((PyObject *)self);
3537 return NULL;
3538 }
3539 return (PyObject *)self;
3540}
