3543/*
3544 _byref consumes a refcount to its argument
3545*/
3546static PyObject *
3547_byref(PyObject *obj)
3548{
3549 PyCArgObject *parg;
3550 if (!CDataObject_Check(obj)) {
3551 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3552 "expected CData instance");
3553 return NULL;
3554 }
3555
3556 parg = PyCArgObject_new();
3557 if (parg == NULL) {
3558 Py_DECREF(obj);
3559 return NULL;
3560 }
3561
3562 parg->tag = 'P';
3563 parg->pffi_type = &ffi_type_pointer;
3564 parg->obj = obj;
3565 parg->value.p = ((CDataObject *)obj)->b_ptr;
3566 return (PyObject *)parg;
3567}
3568
3569static PyObject *
3570_get_arg(int *pindex, PyObject *name, PyObject *defval, PyObject *inargs, PyObject *kwds)
3571{
3572 PyObject *v;
3573
3574 if (*pindex < PyTuple_GET_SIZE(inargs)) {
3575 v = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(inargs, *pindex);
3576 ++*pindex;
3577 Py_INCREF(v);
3578 return v;
3579 }
3580 if (kwds && name && (v = PyDict_GetItem(kwds, name))) {
3581 ++*pindex;
3582 Py_INCREF(v);
3583 return v;
3584 }
3585 if (defval) {
3586 Py_INCREF(defval);
3587 return defval;
3588 }
3589 /* we can't currently emit a better error message */
3590 if (name)
3591 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3592 "required argument '%S' missing", name);
3593 else
3594 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3595 "not enough arguments");
3596 return NULL;
3597}
3598
3599/*
3600 This function implements higher level functionality plus the ability to call
3601 functions with keyword arguments by looking at parameter flags. parameter
3602 flags is a tuple of 1, 2 or 3-tuples. The first entry in each is an integer
3603 specifying the direction of the data transfer for this parameter - 'in',
3604 'out' or 'inout' (zero means the same as 'in'). The second entry is the
3605 parameter name, and the third is the default value if the parameter is
3606 missing in the function call.
3607
3608 This function builds and returns a new tuple 'callargs' which contains the
3609 parameters to use in the call. Items on this tuple are copied from the
3610 'inargs' tuple for 'in' and 'in, out' parameters, and constructed from the
3611 'argtypes' tuple for 'out' parameters. It also calculates numretvals which
3612 is the number of return values for the function, outmask/inoutmask are
3613 bitmasks containing indexes into the callargs tuple specifying which
3614 parameters have to be returned. _build_result builds the return value of the
3615 function.
3616*/
3617static PyObject *
3618_build_callargs(PyCFuncPtrObject *self, PyObject *argtypes,
3619 PyObject *inargs, PyObject *kwds,
3620 int *poutmask, int *pinoutmask, unsigned int *pnumretvals)
3621{
3622 PyObject *paramflags = self->paramflags;
3623 PyObject *callargs;
3624 StgDictObject *dict;
3625 Py_ssize_t i, len;
3626 int inargs_index = 0;
3627 /* It's a little bit difficult to determine how many arguments the
3628 function call requires/accepts. For simplicity, we count the consumed
3629 args and compare this to the number of supplied args. */
3630 Py_ssize_t actual_args;
3631
3632 *poutmask = 0;
3633 *pinoutmask = 0;
3634 *pnumretvals = 0;
3635
3636 /* Trivial cases, where we either return inargs itself, or a slice of it. */
3637 if (argtypes == NULL || paramflags == NULL || PyTuple_GET_SIZE(argtypes) == 0) {
3638#ifdef MS_WIN32
3639 if (self->index)
3640 return PyTuple_GetSlice(inargs, 1, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(inargs));
3641#endif
3642 Py_INCREF(inargs);
3643 return inargs;
3644 }
3645
3646 len = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(argtypes);
3647 callargs = PyTuple_New(len); /* the argument tuple we build */
3648 if (callargs == NULL)
3649 return NULL;
3650
3651#ifdef MS_WIN32
3652 /* For a COM method, skip the first arg */
3653 if (self->index) {
3654 inargs_index = 1;
3655 }
3656#endif
3657 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
3658 PyObject *item = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(paramflags, i);
3659 PyObject *ob;
3660 int flag;
3661 PyObject *name = NULL;
3662 PyObject *defval = NULL;
3663
3664 /* This way seems to be ~2 us faster than the PyArg_ParseTuple
3665 calls below. */
3666 /* We HAVE already checked that the tuple can be parsed with "i|ZO", so... */
3667 Py_ssize_t tsize = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(item);
3668 flag = PyLong_AS_LONG(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(item, 0));
3669 name = tsize > 1 ? PyTuple_GET_ITEM(item, 1) : NULL;
3670 defval = tsize > 2 ? PyTuple_GET_ITEM(item, 2) : NULL;
3671
3672 switch (flag & (PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FOUT | PARAMFLAG_FLCID)) {
3673 case PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FLCID:
3674 /* ['in', 'lcid'] parameter. Always taken from defval,
3675 if given, else the integer 0. */
3676 if (defval == NULL)
3677 defval = _PyLong_Zero;
3678 Py_INCREF(defval);
3679 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(callargs, i, defval);
3680 break;
3681 case (PARAMFLAG_FIN | PARAMFLAG_FOUT):
3682 *pinoutmask |= (1 << i); /* mark as inout arg */
3683 (*pnumretvals)++;
3684 /* fall through */
3685 case 0:
3686 case PARAMFLAG_FIN:
3687 /* 'in' parameter. Copy it from inargs. */
3688 ob =_get_arg(&inargs_index, name, defval, inargs, kwds);
3689 if (ob == NULL)
3690 goto error;
3691 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(callargs, i, ob);
3692 break;
3693 case PARAMFLAG_FOUT:
3694 /* XXX Refactor this code into a separate function. */
3695 /* 'out' parameter.
3696 argtypes[i] must be a POINTER to a c type.
3697
3698 Cannot by supplied in inargs, but a defval will be used
3699 if available. XXX Should we support getting it from kwds?
3700 */
3701 if (defval) {
3702 /* XXX Using mutable objects as defval will
3703 make the function non-threadsafe, unless we
3704 copy the object in each invocation */
3705 Py_INCREF(defval);
3706 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(callargs, i, defval);
3707 *poutmask |= (1 << i); /* mark as out arg */
3708 (*pnumretvals)++;
3709 break;
3710 }
3711 ob = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argtypes, i);
3712 dict = PyType_stgdict(ob);
3713 if (dict == NULL) {
3714 /* Cannot happen: _validate_paramflags()
3715 would not accept such an object */
3716 PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3717 "NULL stgdict unexpected");
3718 goto error;
3719 }
3720 if (PyUnicode_Check(dict->proto)) {
3721 PyErr_Format(
3722 PyExc_TypeError,
3723 "%s 'out' parameter must be passed as default value",
3724 ((PyTypeObject *)ob)->tp_name);
3725 goto error;
3726 }
3727 if (PyCArrayTypeObject_Check(ob))
3728 ob = _PyObject_CallNoArg(ob);
3729 else
3730 /* Create an instance of the pointed-to type */
3731 ob = _PyObject_CallNoArg(dict->proto);
3732 /*
3733 XXX Is the following correct any longer?
3734 We must not pass a byref() to the array then but
3735 the array instance itself. Then, we cannot retrive
3736 the result from the PyCArgObject.
3737 */
3738 if (ob == NULL)
3739 goto error;
3740 /* The .from_param call that will occur later will pass this
3741 as a byref parameter. */
3742 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(callargs, i, ob);
3743 *poutmask |= (1 << i); /* mark as out arg */
3744 (*pnumretvals)++;
3745 break;
3746 default:
3747 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
3748 "paramflag %d not yet implemented", flag);
3749 goto error;
3750 break;
3751 }
3752 }
3753
3754 /* We have counted the arguments we have consumed in 'inargs_index'. This
3755 must be the same as len(inargs) + len(kwds), otherwise we have
3756 either too much or not enough arguments. */
3757
3758 actual_args = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(inargs) + (kwds ? PyDict_GET_SIZE(kwds) : 0);
3759 if (actual_args != inargs_index) {
3760 /* When we have default values or named parameters, this error
3761 message is misleading. See unittests/test_paramflags.py
3762 */
3763 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3764 "call takes exactly %d arguments (%zd given)",
3765 inargs_index, actual_args);
3766 goto error;
3767 }
3768
3769 /* outmask is a bitmask containing indexes into callargs. Items at
3770 these indexes contain values to return.
3771 */
3772 return callargs;
3773 error:
3774 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3775 return NULL;
3776}
3777
3778/* See also:
3779 http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/com/html/769127a1-1a14-4ed4-9d38-7cf3e571b661.asp
3780*/
3781/*
3782 Build return value of a function.
3783
3784 Consumes the refcount on result and callargs.
3785*/
3786static PyObject *
3787_build_result(PyObject *result, PyObject *callargs,
3788 int outmask, int inoutmask, unsigned int numretvals)
3789{
3790 unsigned int i, index;
3791 int bit;
3792 PyObject *tup = NULL;
3793
3794 if (callargs == NULL)
3795 return result;
3796 if (result == NULL || numretvals == 0) {
3797 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3798 return result;
3799 }
3800 Py_DECREF(result);
3801
3802 /* tup will not be allocated if numretvals == 1 */
3803 /* allocate tuple to hold the result */
3804 if (numretvals > 1) {
3805 tup = PyTuple_New(numretvals);
3806 if (tup == NULL) {
3807 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3808 return NULL;
3809 }
3810 }
3811
3812 index = 0;
3813 for (bit = 1, i = 0; i < 32; ++i, bit <<= 1) {
3814 PyObject *v;
3815 if (bit & inoutmask) {
3816 v = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(callargs, i);
3817 Py_INCREF(v);
3818 if (numretvals == 1) {
3819 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3820 return v;
3821 }
3822 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(tup, index, v);
3823 index++;
3824 } else if (bit & outmask) {
3825 _Py_IDENTIFIER(__ctypes_from_outparam__);
3826
3827 v = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(callargs, i);
3828 v = _PyObject_CallMethodId(v, &PyId___ctypes_from_outparam__, NULL);
3829 if (v == NULL || numretvals == 1) {
3830 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3831 return v;
3832 }
3833 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(tup, index, v);
3834 index++;
3835 }
3836 if (index == numretvals)
3837 break;
3838 }
3839
3840 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3841 return tup;
3842}
3843
3844static PyObject *
3845PyCFuncPtr_call(PyCFuncPtrObject *self, PyObject *inargs, PyObject *kwds)
3846{
3847 PyObject *restype;
3848 PyObject *converters;
3849 PyObject *checker;
3850 PyObject *argtypes;
3851 StgDictObject *dict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
3852 PyObject *result;
3853 PyObject *callargs;
3854 PyObject *errcheck;
3855#ifdef MS_WIN32
3856 IUnknown *piunk = NULL;
3857#endif
3858 void *pProc = NULL;
3859
3860 int inoutmask;
3861 int outmask;
3862 unsigned int numretvals;
3863
3864 assert(dict); /* Cannot be NULL for PyCFuncPtrObject instances */
3865 restype = self->restype ? self->restype : dict->restype;
3866 converters = self->converters ? self->converters : dict->converters;
3867 checker = self->checker ? self->checker : dict->checker;
3868 argtypes = self->argtypes ? self->argtypes : dict->argtypes;
3869/* later, we probably want to have an errcheck field in stgdict */
3870 errcheck = self->errcheck /* ? self->errcheck : dict->errcheck */;
3871
3872
3873 pProc = *(void **)self->b_ptr;
3874#ifdef MS_WIN32
3875 if (self->index) {
3876 /* It's a COM method */
3877 CDataObject *this;
3878 this = (CDataObject *)PyTuple_GetItem(inargs, 0); /* borrowed ref! */
3879 if (!this) {
3880 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
3881 "native com method call without 'this' parameter");
3882 return NULL;
3883 }
3884 if (!CDataObject_Check(this)) {
3885 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3886 "Expected a COM this pointer as first argument");
3887 return NULL;
3888 }
3889 /* there should be more checks? No, in Python */
3890 /* First arg is a pointer to an interface instance */
3891 if (!this->b_ptr || *(void **)this->b_ptr == NULL) {
3892 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
3893 "NULL COM pointer access");
3894 return NULL;
3895 }
3896 piunk = *(IUnknown **)this->b_ptr;
3897 if (NULL == piunk->lpVtbl) {
3898 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
3899 "COM method call without VTable");
3900 return NULL;
3901 }
3902 pProc = ((void **)piunk->lpVtbl)[self->index - 0x1000];
3903 }
3904#endif
3905 callargs = _build_callargs(self, argtypes,
3906 inargs, kwds,
3907 &outmask, &inoutmask, &numretvals);
3908 if (callargs == NULL)
3909 return NULL;
3910
3911 if (converters) {
3912 int required = Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(converters),
3913 Py_ssize_t, int);
3914 int actual = Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(PyTuple_GET_SIZE(callargs),
3915 Py_ssize_t, int);
3916
3917 if ((dict->flags & FUNCFLAG_CDECL) == FUNCFLAG_CDECL) {
3918 /* For cdecl functions, we allow more actual arguments
3919 than the length of the argtypes tuple.
3920 */
3921 if (required > actual) {
3922 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3923 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3924 "this function takes at least %d argument%s (%d given)",
3925 required,
3926 required == 1 ? "" : "s",
3927 actual);
3928 return NULL;
3929 }
3930 } else if (required != actual) {
3931 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3932 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
3933 "this function takes %d argument%s (%d given)",
3934 required,
3935 required == 1 ? "" : "s",
3936 actual);
3937 return NULL;
3938 }
3939 }
3940
3941 result = _ctypes_callproc(pProc,
3942 callargs,
3943#ifdef MS_WIN32
3944 piunk,
3945 self->iid,
3946#endif
3947 dict->flags,
3948 converters,
3949 restype,
3950 checker);
3951/* The 'errcheck' protocol */
3952 if (result != NULL && errcheck) {
3953 PyObject *v = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(errcheck,
3954 result,
3955 self,
3956 callargs,
3957 NULL);
3958 /* If the errcheck function failed, return NULL.
3959 If the errcheck function returned callargs unchanged,
3960 continue normal processing.
3961 If the errcheck function returned something else,
3962 use that as result.
3963 */
3964 if (v == NULL || v != callargs) {
3965 Py_DECREF(result);
3966 Py_DECREF(callargs);
3967 return v;
3968 }
3969 Py_DECREF(v);
3970 }
3971
3972 return _build_result(result, callargs,
3973 outmask, inoutmask, numretvals);
3974}

4091/*****************************************************************/
4092/*
4093 Struct_Type
4094*/
4095/*
4096 This function is called to initialize a Structure or Union with positional
4097 arguments. It calls itself recursively for all Structure or Union base
4098 classes, then retrieves the _fields_ member to associate the argument
4099 position with the correct field name.
4100
4101 Returns -1 on error, or the index of next argument on success.
4102 */
4103static Py_ssize_t
4104_init_pos_args(PyObject *self, PyTypeObject *type,
4105 PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds,
4106 Py_ssize_t index)
4107{
4108 StgDictObject *dict;
4109 PyObject *fields;
4110 Py_ssize_t i;
4111
4112 if (PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)type->tp_base)) {
4113 index = _init_pos_args(self, type->tp_base,
4114 args, kwds,
4115 index);
4116 if (index == -1)
4117 return -1;
4118 }
4119
4120 dict = PyType_stgdict((PyObject *)type);
4121 fields = PyDict_GetItemString((PyObject *)dict, "_fields_");
4122 if (fields == NULL)
4123 return index;
4124
4125 for (i = 0;
4126 i < dict->length && (i+index) < PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args);
4127 ++i) {
4128 PyObject *pair = PySequence_GetItem(fields, i);
4129 PyObject *name, *val;
4130 int res;
4131 if (!pair)
4132 return -1;
4133 name = PySequence_GetItem(pair, 0);
4134 if (!name) {
4135 Py_DECREF(pair);
4136 return -1;
4137 }
4138 val = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, i + index);
4139 if (kwds && PyDict_GetItem(kwds, name)) {
4140 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4141 "duplicate values for field %R",
4142 name);
4143 Py_DECREF(pair);
4144 Py_DECREF(name);
4145 return -1;
4146 }
4147
4148 res = PyObject_SetAttr(self, name, val);
4149 Py_DECREF(pair);
4150 Py_DECREF(name);
4151 if (res == -1)
4152 return -1;
4153 }
4154 return index + dict->length;
4155}
4156
4157static int
4158Struct_init(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwds)
4159{
4160/* Optimization possible: Store the attribute names _fields_[x][0]
4161 * in C accessible fields somewhere ?
4162 */
4163 if (!PyTuple_Check(args)) {
4164 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4165 "args not a tuple?");
4166 return -1;
4167 }
4168 if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args)) {
4169 Py_ssize_t res = _init_pos_args(self, Py_TYPE(self),
4170 args, kwds, 0);
4171 if (res == -1)
4172 return -1;
4173 if (res < PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args)) {
4174 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4175 "too many initializers");
4176 return -1;
4177 }
4178 }
4179
4180 if (kwds) {
4181 PyObject *key, *value;
4182 Py_ssize_t pos = 0;

4184 if (-1 == PyObject_SetAttr(self, key, value))
4185 return -1;
4186 }
4187 }
4188 return 0;
4189}

4282{

4285

4292 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
4293 PyObject *v;

4297 }

4299}

4301static PyObject *
4302Array_item(PyObject *myself, Py_ssize_t index)
4303{
4304 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4305 Py_ssize_t offset, size;
4306 StgDictObject *stgdict;
4307
4308
4309 if (index < 0 || index >= self->b_length) {
4310 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError,
4311 "invalid index");
4312 return NULL;
4313 }
4314
4315 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4316 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for array instances */
4317 /* Would it be clearer if we got the item size from
4318 stgdict->proto's stgdict?
4319 */
4320 size = stgdict->size / stgdict->length;
4321 offset = index * size;
4322
4323 return PyCData_get(stgdict->proto, stgdict->getfunc, (PyObject *)self,
4324 index, size, self->b_ptr + offset);
4325}
4326
4327static PyObject *
4328Array_subscript(PyObject *myself, PyObject *item)
4329{
4330 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4331
4332 if (PyIndex_Check(item)) {
4333 Py_ssize_t i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(item, PyExc_IndexError);
4334
4335 if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
4336 return NULL;
4337 if (i < 0)
4338 i += self->b_length;
4339 return Array_item(myself, i);
4340 }
4341 else if (PySlice_Check(item)) {
4342 StgDictObject *stgdict, *itemdict;
4343 PyObject *proto;
4344 PyObject *np;
4345 Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelen, cur, i;
4346
4347 if (PySlice_Unpack(item, &start, &stop, &step) < 0) {
4348 return NULL;
4349 }
4350 slicelen = PySlice_AdjustIndices(self->b_length, &start, &stop, step);
4351
4352 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4353 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for array object instances */
4354 proto = stgdict->proto;
4355 itemdict = PyType_stgdict(proto);
4356 assert(itemdict); /* proto is the item type of the array, a
4357 ctypes type, so this cannot be NULL */
4358
4359 if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("c")->getfunc) {
4360 char *ptr = (char *)self->b_ptr;
4361 char *dest;
4362
4363 if (slicelen <= 0)
4364 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize("", 0);
4365 if (step == 1) {
4366 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(ptr + start,
4367 slicelen);
4368 }
4369 dest = (char *)PyMem_Malloc(slicelen);
4370
4371 if (dest == NULL)
4372 return PyErr_NoMemory();
4373
4374 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < slicelen;
4375 cur += step, i++) {
4376 dest[i] = ptr[cur];
4377 }
4378
4379 np = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(dest, slicelen);
4380 PyMem_Free(dest);
4381 return np;
4382 }
4383#ifdef CTYPES_UNICODE
4384 if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("u")->getfunc) {
4385 wchar_t *ptr = (wchar_t *)self->b_ptr;
4386 wchar_t *dest;
4387
4388 if (slicelen <= 0)
4389 return PyUnicode_New(0, 0);
4390 if (step == 1) {
4391 return PyUnicode_FromWideChar(ptr + start,
4392 slicelen);
4393 }
4394
4395 dest = PyMem_New(wchar_t, slicelen);
4396 if (dest == NULL) {
4397 PyErr_NoMemory();
4398 return NULL;
4399 }
4400
4401 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < slicelen;
4402 cur += step, i++) {
4403 dest[i] = ptr[cur];
4404 }
4405
4406 np = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(dest, slicelen);
4407 PyMem_Free(dest);
4408 return np;
4409 }
4410#endif
4411
4412 np = PyList_New(slicelen);
4413 if (np == NULL)
4414 return NULL;
4415
4416 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < slicelen;
4417 cur += step, i++) {
4418 PyObject *v = Array_item(myself, cur);
4419 if (v == NULL) {
4420 Py_DECREF(np);
4421 return NULL;
4422 }
4423 PyList_SET_ITEM(np, i, v);
4424 }
4425 return np;
4426 }
4427 else {
4428 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4429 "indices must be integers");
4430 return NULL;
4431 }
4432
4433}

4435static int
4436Array_ass_item(PyObject *myself, Py_ssize_t index, PyObject *value)
4437{
4438 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4439 Py_ssize_t size, offset;
4440 StgDictObject *stgdict;
4441 char *ptr;
4442
4443 if (value == NULL) {
4444 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4445 "Array does not support item deletion");
4446 return -1;
4447 }
4448
4449 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4450 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for array object instances */
4451 if (index < 0 || index >= stgdict->length) {
4452 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError,
4453 "invalid index");
4454 return -1;
4455 }
4456 size = stgdict->size / stgdict->length;
4457 offset = index * size;
4458 ptr = self->b_ptr + offset;
4459
4460 return PyCData_set((PyObject *)self, stgdict->proto, stgdict->setfunc, value,
4461 index, size, ptr);

4464static int
4465Array_ass_subscript(PyObject *myself, PyObject *item, PyObject *value)
4466{
4467 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4468
4469 if (value == NULL) {
4470 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4471 "Array does not support item deletion");
4472 return -1;
4473 }
4474
4475 if (PyIndex_Check(item)) {
4476 Py_ssize_t i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(item, PyExc_IndexError);
4477
4478 if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
4479 return -1;
4480 if (i < 0)
4481 i += self->b_length;
4482 return Array_ass_item(myself, i, value);
4483 }
4484 else if (PySlice_Check(item)) {
4485 Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelen, otherlen, i, cur;
4486
4487 if (PySlice_Unpack(item, &start, &stop, &step) < 0) {
4488 return -1;
4489 }
4490 slicelen = PySlice_AdjustIndices(self->b_length, &start, &stop, step);
4491 if ((step < 0 && start < stop) ||
4492 (step > 0 && start > stop))
4493 stop = start;
4494
4495 otherlen = PySequence_Length(value);
4496 if (otherlen != slicelen) {
4497 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4498 "Can only assign sequence of same size");
4499 return -1;
4500 }
4501 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < otherlen; cur += step, i++) {
4502 PyObject *item = PySequence_GetItem(value, i);
4503 int result;
4504 if (item == NULL)
4505 return -1;
4506 result = Array_ass_item(myself, cur, item);
4507 Py_DECREF(item);
4508 if (result == -1)
4509 return -1;
4510 }
4511 return 0;
4512 }
4513 else {
4514 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4515 "indices must be integer");
4516 return -1;
4517 }
4518}

4589PyObject *
4590PyCArrayType_from_ctype(PyObject *itemtype, Py_ssize_t length)
4591{
4592 static PyObject *cache;
4593 PyObject *key;
4594 PyObject *result;
4595 char name[256];
4596 PyObject *len;
4597
4598 if (cache == NULL) {
4599 cache = PyDict_New();
4600 if (cache == NULL)
4601 return NULL;
4602 }
4603 len = PyLong_FromSsize_t(length);
4604 if (len == NULL)
4605 return NULL;
4606 key = PyTuple_Pack(2, itemtype, len);
4607 Py_DECREF(len);
4608 if (!key)
4609 return NULL;
4610 result = PyDict_GetItemProxy(cache, key);
4611 if (result) {
4612 Py_INCREF(result);
4613 Py_DECREF(key);
4614 return result;
4615 }
4616
4617 if (!PyType_Check(itemtype)) {
4618 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4619 "Expected a type object");
4620 Py_DECREF(key);
4621 return NULL;
4622 }
4623#ifdef MS_WIN64
4624 sprintf(name, "%.200s_Array_%Id",
4625 ((PyTypeObject *)itemtype)->tp_name, length);
4626#else
4627 sprintf(name, "%.200s_Array_%ld",
4628 ((PyTypeObject *)itemtype)->tp_name, (long)length);
4629#endif
4630
4631 result = PyObject_CallFunction((PyObject *)&PyCArrayType_Type,
4632 "s(O){s:n,s:O}",
4633 name,
4634 &PyCArray_Type,
4635 "_length_",
4636 length,
4637 "_type_",
4638 itemtype
4639 );
4640 if (result == NULL) {
4641 Py_DECREF(key);
4642 return NULL;
4643 }
4644 if (-1 == PyDict_SetItemProxy(cache, key, result)) {
4645 Py_DECREF(key);
4646 Py_DECREF(result);
4647 return NULL;
4648 }
4649 Py_DECREF(key);
4650 return result;
4651}

4839static int
4840Pointer_ass_item(PyObject *myself, Py_ssize_t index, PyObject *value)
4841{
4842 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4843 Py_ssize_t size;
4844 Py_ssize_t offset;
4845 StgDictObject *stgdict, *itemdict;
4846 PyObject *proto;
4847
4848 if (value == NULL) {
4849 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4850 "Pointer does not support item deletion");
4851 return -1;
4852 }
4853
4854 if (*(void **)self->b_ptr == NULL) {
4855 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4856 "NULL pointer access");
4857 return -1;
4858 }
4859
4860 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4861 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer instances */
4862
4863 proto = stgdict->proto;
4864 assert(proto);
4865
4866 itemdict = PyType_stgdict(proto);
4867 assert(itemdict); /* Cannot be NULL because the itemtype of a pointer

4869
4870 size = itemdict->size;
4871 offset = index * itemdict->size;
4872
4873 return PyCData_set((PyObject *)self, proto, stgdict->setfunc, value,
4874 index, size, (*(char **)self->b_ptr) + offset);
4875}
4876
4877static PyObject *
4878Pointer_get_contents(CDataObject *self, void *closure)
4879{
4880 StgDictObject *stgdict;
4881
4882 if (*(void **)self->b_ptr == NULL) {
4883 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4884 "NULL pointer access");
4885 return NULL;
4886 }
4887
4888 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4889 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer instances */
4890 return PyCData_FromBaseObj(stgdict->proto,
4891 (PyObject *)self, 0,
4892 *(void **)self->b_ptr);
4893}
4894
4895static int
4896Pointer_set_contents(CDataObject *self, PyObject *value, void *closure)
4897{
4898 StgDictObject *stgdict;
4899 CDataObject *dst;
4900 PyObject *keep;
4901
4902 if (value == NULL) {
4903 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4904 "Pointer does not support item deletion");
4905 return -1;
4906 }
4907 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
4908 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer instances */
4909 assert(stgdict->proto);
4910 if (!CDataObject_Check(value)) {
4911 int res = PyObject_IsInstance(value, stgdict->proto);
4912 if (res == -1)
4913 return -1;
4914 if (!res) {
4915 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4916 "expected %s instead of %s",
4917 ((PyTypeObject *)(stgdict->proto))->tp_name,
4918 Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
4919 return -1;
4920 }
4921 }
4922
4923 dst = (CDataObject *)value;
4924 *(void **)self->b_ptr = dst->b_ptr;
4925
4926 /*
4927 A Pointer instance must keep the value it points to alive. So, a
4928 pointer instance has b_length set to 2 instead of 1, and we set
4929 'value' itself as the second item of the b_objects list, additionally.
4930 */
4931 Py_INCREF(value);
4932 if (-1 == KeepRef(self, 1, value))
4933 return -1;
4934
4935 keep = GetKeepedObjects(dst);
4936 if (keep == NULL)
4937 return -1;
4938
4939 Py_INCREF(keep);
4940 return KeepRef(self, 0, keep);
4941}

4947 { NULL, NULL }
4948};

4956 return -1;

4973
4974static PyObject *
4975Pointer_subscript(PyObject *myself, PyObject *item)
4976{
4977 CDataObject *self = (CDataObject *)myself;
4978 if (PyIndex_Check(item)) {
4979 Py_ssize_t i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(item, PyExc_IndexError);
4980 if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
4981 return NULL;
4982 return Pointer_item(myself, i);
4983 }
4984 else if (PySlice_Check(item)) {
4985 PySliceObject *slice = (PySliceObject *)item;
4986 Py_ssize_t start, stop, step;
4987 PyObject *np;
4988 StgDictObject *stgdict, *itemdict;
4989 PyObject *proto;
4990 Py_ssize_t i, len, cur;
4991
4992 /* Since pointers have no length, and we want to apply
4993 different semantics to negative indices than normal
4994 slicing, we have to dissect the slice object ourselves.*/
4995 if (slice->step == Py_None) {
4996 step = 1;
4997 }
4998 else {
4999 step = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(slice->step,
5000 PyExc_ValueError);
5001 if (step == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
5002 return NULL;
5003 if (step == 0) {
5004 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
5005 "slice step cannot be zero");
5006 return NULL;
5007 }
5008 }
5009 if (slice->start == Py_None) {
5010 if (step < 0) {
5011 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
5012 "slice start is required "
5013 "for step < 0");
5014 return NULL;
5015 }
5016 start = 0;
5017 }
5018 else {
5019 start = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(slice->start,
5020 PyExc_ValueError);
5021 if (start == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
5022 return NULL;
5023 }
5024 if (slice->stop == Py_None) {
5025 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
5026 "slice stop is required");
5027 return NULL;
5028 }
5029 stop = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(slice->stop,
5030 PyExc_ValueError);
5031 if (stop == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
5032 return NULL;
5033 if ((step > 0 && start > stop) ||
5034 (step < 0 && start < stop))
5035 len = 0;
5036 else if (step > 0)
5037 len = (stop - start - 1) / step + 1;
5038 else
5039 len = (stop - start + 1) / step + 1;
5040
5041 stgdict = PyObject_stgdict((PyObject *)self);
5042 assert(stgdict); /* Cannot be NULL for pointer instances */
5043 proto = stgdict->proto;
5044 assert(proto);
5045 itemdict = PyType_stgdict(proto);
5046 assert(itemdict);
5047 if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("c")->getfunc) {
5048 char *ptr = *(char **)self->b_ptr;
5049 char *dest;
5050
5051 if (len <= 0)
5052 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize("", 0);
5053 if (step == 1) {
5054 return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(ptr + start,
5055 len);
5056 }
5057 dest = (char *)PyMem_Malloc(len);
5058 if (dest == NULL)
5059 return PyErr_NoMemory();
5060 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < len; cur += step, i++) {
5061 dest[i] = ptr[cur];
5062 }
5063 np = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(dest, len);
5064 PyMem_Free(dest);
5065 return np;
5066 }
5067#ifdef CTYPES_UNICODE
5068 if (itemdict->getfunc == _ctypes_get_fielddesc("u")->getfunc) {
5069 wchar_t *ptr = *(wchar_t **)self->b_ptr;
5070 wchar_t *dest;
5071
5072 if (len <= 0)
5073 return PyUnicode_New(0, 0);
5074 if (step == 1) {
5075 return PyUnicode_FromWideChar(ptr + start,
5076 len);
5077 }
5078 dest = PyMem_New(wchar_t, len);
5079 if (dest == NULL)
5080 return PyErr_NoMemory();
5081 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < len; cur += step, i++) {
5082 dest[i] = ptr[cur];
5083 }
5084 np = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(dest, len);
5085 PyMem_Free(dest);
5086 return np;
5087 }
5088#endif
5089
5090 np = PyList_New(len);
5091 if (np == NULL)
5092 return NULL;
5093
5094 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < len; cur += step, i++) {
5095 PyObject *v = Pointer_item(myself, cur);
5096 PyList_SET_ITEM(np, i, v);
5097 }
5098 return np;
5099 }
5100 else {
5101 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5102 "Pointer indices must be integer");
5103 return NULL;
5104 }
5105}

5299static int
5300cast_check_pointertype(PyObject *arg)
5301{
5302 StgDictObject *dict;
5303
5304 if (PyCPointerTypeObject_Check(arg))
5305 return 1;
5306 if (PyCFuncPtrTypeObject_Check(arg))
5307 return 1;
5308 dict = PyType_stgdict(arg);
5309 if (dict) {
5310 if (PyUnicode_Check(dict->proto)
5311 && (strchr("sPzUZXO", PyUnicode_AsUTF8(dict->proto)[0]))) {
5312 /* simple pointer types, c_void_p, c_wchar_p, BSTR, ... */
5313 return 1;
5314 }
5315 }
5316 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
5317 "cast() argument 2 must be a pointer type, not %s",
5318 PyType_Check(arg)
5319 ? ((PyTypeObject *)arg)->tp_name
5320 : Py_TYPE(arg)->tp_name);
5321 return 0;
5322}
5323
5324static PyObject *
5325cast(void *ptr, PyObject *src, PyObject *ctype)
5326{
5327 CDataObject *result;
5328 if (0 == cast_check_pointertype(ctype))
5329 return NULL;
5330 result = (CDataObject *)_PyObject_CallNoArg(ctype);
5331 if (result == NULL)
5332 return NULL;
5333
5334 /*
5335 The casted objects '_objects' member:
5336
5337 It must certainly contain the source objects one.
5338 It must contain the source object itself.
5339 */
5340 if (CDataObject_Check(src)) {
5341 CDataObject *obj = (CDataObject *)src;
5342 CDataObject *container;
5343
5344 /* PyCData_GetContainer will initialize src.b_objects, we need
5345 this so it can be shared */
5346 container = PyCData_GetContainer(obj);
5347 if (container == NULL)
5348 goto failed;
5349
5350 /* But we need a dictionary! */
5351 if (obj->b_objects == Py_None) {
5352 Py_DECREF(Py_None);
5353 obj->b_objects = PyDict_New();
5354 if (obj->b_objects == NULL)
5355 goto failed;
5356 }
5357 Py_XINCREF(obj->b_objects);
5358 result->b_objects = obj->b_objects;
5359 if (result->b_objects && PyDict_CheckExact(result->b_objects)) {
5360 PyObject *index;
5361 int rc;
5362 index = PyLong_FromVoidPtr((void *)src);
5363 if (index == NULL)
5364 goto failed;
5365 rc = PyDict_SetItem(result->b_objects, index, src);
5366 Py_DECREF(index);
5367 if (rc == -1)
5368 goto failed;
5369 }
5370 }
5371 /* Should we assert that result is a pointer type? */
5372 memcpy(result->b_ptr, &ptr, sizeof(void *));
5373 return (PyObject *)result;
5374
5375 failed:
5376 Py_DECREF(result);
5377 return NULL;
5378}

5550 PyModule_AddStringConstant(m, "__version__", "1.1.0");
5551
5552 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_memmove_addr", PyLong_FromVoidPtr(memmove));
5553 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_memset_addr", PyLong_FromVoidPtr(memset));
5554 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_string_at_addr", PyLong_FromVoidPtr(string_at));
5555 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_cast_addr", PyLong_FromVoidPtr(cast));
5556#ifdef CTYPES_UNICODE
5557 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_wstring_at_addr", PyLong_FromVoidPtr(wstring_at));
5558#endif
5559
5560/* If RTLD_LOCAL is not defined (Windows!), set it to zero. */
5561#if !HAVE_DECL_RTLD_LOCAL
5562#define RTLD_LOCAL 0
5563#endif
5564
5565/* If RTLD_GLOBAL is not defined (cygwin), set it to the same value as
5566 RTLD_LOCAL.
5567*/
5568#if !HAVE_DECL_RTLD_GLOBAL
5569#define RTLD_GLOBAL RTLD_LOCAL
5570#endif
5571
5572 PyModule_AddObject(m, "RTLD_LOCAL", PyLong_FromLong(RTLD_LOCAL));
5573 PyModule_AddObject(m, "RTLD_GLOBAL", PyLong_FromLong(RTLD_GLOBAL));
5574
5575 PyExc_ArgError = PyErr_NewException("ctypes.ArgumentError", NULL, NULL);
5576 if (PyExc_ArgError) {
5577 Py_INCREF(PyExc_ArgError);
5578 PyModule_AddObject(m, "ArgumentError", PyExc_ArgError);
5579 }
5580 return m;
5581}
